Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.00,0:04:07.81,英文,,0,0,0,,Alright, this is CS50. Welcome to week 8, last week. We learned how to create, read, update, and delete databases using SQL. But this week, we're going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.81,0:04:11.20,英文,,0,0,0,,SETH LADD. Adam, everyone. Happy Halloween.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.16,0:04:23.30,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so this is CS50, and this is week eight already.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.30,0:04:27.24,英文,,0,0,0,,My thanks to Adam on today, this happy Halloween.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:37.15,英文,,0,0,0,,In the coming moments, we're going to learn all about how the internet itself works, which, of course, is a technology that we all use every day, probably using in some form right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.15,0:04:44.84,英文,,0,0,0,,But we'll see that if you start to understand some of the underlying building blocks that power the internet itself, we can actually start to build interesting things on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.84,0:04:50.79,英文,,0,0,0,,And a lot of the apps, the websites that you all use every day should become all the more familiar, things that you yourselves can create.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.79,0:05:01.10,英文,,0,0,0,,And honestly, when things go wrong, you'll have all the more of a mental model for how things work or are not, in fact, working so that you can ultimately Diagnose all the more issues yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.10,0:05:05.00,英文,,0,0,0,,So if we take a look at the internet in the early days, it pretty much was just this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.00,0:05:07.54,英文,,0,0,0,,This happens to be, of course, the geography of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.54,0:05:12.00,英文,,0,0,0,,And just some of the first points on the internet were these here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:14.73,英文,,0,0,0,,This was so-called ARPANET back in 1969.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.73,0:05:20.87,英文,,0,0,0,,And indeed, the internet had its origins here in the United States with just a few computers interconnected somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.87,0:05:27.22,英文,,0,0,0,,Initially, that, of course, began to grow over time, such that we eventually had the West Coast connected to the East Coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.22,0:05:32.44,英文,,0,0,0,,And nowadays, what you can think of, these dots on the screens it's representing, are these things called routers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.44,0:05:51.21,英文,,0,0,0,,Sort of computers, or really servers, that somehow have wires, or maybe wireless connections between them, that allow data to flow from point A to B to C. And then this, of course, has been now magnified across the entire globe, and even above ground as well, so that we can connect all the more readily to systems anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.21,0:05:57.36,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, in order to route the data from one router to another, we need to somehow make routing decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.36,0:06:02.44,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is the kind of thing that the internet service providers, the ISPs of the world, just handle for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.44,0:06:10.60,英文,,0,0,0,,You and I plug our Macs, our PCs, into the network here at Harvard, or equivalently at Yale, or we somehow get online via Wi-Fi or cellular technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:17.99,英文,,0,0,0,,And then some of these larger entities, these bigger companies or countries, handle most of the data getting from point A to point B.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.99,0:06:26.97,英文,,0,0,0,,And if you think about what these routers represent, they're indeed just servers somehow interconnected, not unlike this grid of tiles here, for instance, back in the Zoom days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.97,0:06:33.71,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, here we have, I claim, a grid of routers implemented here by the course's teaching fellows and course assistants and TAs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.71,0:06:45.58,英文,,0,0,0,,And if the goal at hand, for instance, is for Phyllis to route some piece of information, maybe it's an email, maybe it's a request for a web page in the bottom right-hand corner, all the way up to, say, Brian here in the top left-hand corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.58,0:06:52.30,英文,,0,0,0,,Suffice it to say, each of these tiles represents a router, a server that can move the data back, forth, left, and right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.30,0:07:01.57,英文,,0,0,0,,That packet of information, so to speak, from Phyllis to Brian could take any number of different possible routes, up, down, left, right, to go from the one corner to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.57,0:07:06.47,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me go ahead and hit Play on this video here, wherein the teaching fellows play this same role.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.45,0:07:27.55,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so in this particular case, the data was routed pretty straightforwardly up and then to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.55,0:07:30.01,英文,,0,0,0,,But suppose that one or more of the staff were a bit busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.01,0:07:32.31,英文,,0,0,0,,Maybe one of the routers is congested.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:36.36,英文,,0,0,0,,That is to say, just got way more envelopes at a moment in time than it can handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.36,0:07:42.24,英文,,0,0,0,,Thankfully, the design of the internet is such that there's often multiple ways that data can get from point A to point B.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.24,0:07:45.00,英文,,0,0,0,,Maybe going through point C or point D instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.00,0:07:49.43,英文,,0,0,0,,And so there's a resilience there, even as some of these servers themselves might go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.43,0:07:55.96,英文,,0,0,0,,So allow me to propose that we use the same grid of routers now to route the data in a slightly different way this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:25.09,英文,,0,0,0,,So success.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.09,0:08:29.07,英文,,0,0,0,,You'll see perhaps later just how many takes it took us to actually get that routing right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.07,0:08:43.36,英文,,0,0,0,,But it does, in fact, manifest that you can travel different paths in order to get the data from point A to point B. So as we talk about routers, as you think of the internet, I mean, think of those humans as just representing these routers, points A to B and everywhere in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.36,0:08:50.91,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, how did the teaching staff know to route that packet up and then down or left and right in order to get to the destination?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.91,0:08:54.39,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, all of them were programmed, so to speak, to understand protocols.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.39,0:08:59.47,英文,,0,0,0,,It's called TCP and IP, otherwise known together typically as TCP slash IP.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.47,0:09:07.26,英文,,0,0,0,,And you've probably seen these acronyms at some point in the real world, on the internet, on some kind of documentation, a text, even if you haven't really thought hard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.26,0:09:11.08,英文,,0,0,0,,But IP is certainly the more common of the two, perhaps. In common culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.08,0:09:13.10,英文,,0,0,0,,So what does TCP and IP do for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.10,0:09:15.30,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, really two primary things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.30,0:09:22.24,英文,,0,0,0,,Any computer or any teaching staff member who understands TCP IP knows how to get data from point A to point B. But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.24,0:09:25.32,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, let's break down what that problem to be solved is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.32,0:09:32.20,英文,,0,0,0,,IP, otherwise known as Internet Protocol, is a protocol that computers speak that allow them to know how to address computers on the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.20,0:09:38.23,英文,,0,0,0,,And a protocol is just a set of conventions that computers adhere to.So someone wrote code that probably has a whole lot of conditionals that tells the computer what to do if something happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.23,0:09:45.59,英文,,0,0,0,,Like if I receive a packet, then send it to the next server or something like that. In the human world, we have protocols too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.59,0:09:55.37,英文,,0,0,0,,In healthier times, it was quite common to sort of extend your hand to another human in order to greet them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.37,0:10:02.77,英文,,0,0,0,,And if they're following human protocol, they would presumably grab your hand and shake it, at least in a culture like this one here on campus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.77,0:10:09.03,英文,,0,0,0,,And now that is a human protocol in that someone initiates it, someone responds to it, and you both sort of know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.03,0:10:10.28,英文,,0,0,0,,You're programmed to know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.28,0:10:12.52,英文,,0,0,0,,So same idea with internet protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.52,0:10:16.92,英文,,0,0,0,,Computers just know what to do when they've been programmed to do so. So what does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.92,0:10:32.23,英文,,0,0,0,,If IP decides that every computer in the world will have a unique address, just like the Science Center around the corner might have a unique address of 1 Oxford Street, Cambridge, Massachusetts, 02138USA.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.23,0:10:36.49,英文,,0,0,0,,IP dictates that every computer on the internet have a unique address of this form.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.49,0:10:40.84,英文,,0,0,0,,And this, too, is probably something you've seen in the real world, even if you haven't thought too hard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.84,0:10:47.44,英文,,0,0,0,,It's a number in what's called dotted decimal notation, which means it's a decimal number, dot something, dot something, dot something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.44,0:10:54.02,英文,,0,0,0,,So four digits separated by convention by decimal points, although, There are newer and bigger versions of the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.02,0:11:02.67,英文,,0,0,0,,And these so-called IP addresses that might be as simple as 1.2.3.4 uniquely identify a computer on the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.67,0:11:07.37,英文,,0,0,0,,The numbers have to range from 0 to 255 each.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.37,0:11:10.31,英文,,0,0,0,,And that's a bit of a hint just as you start to think more computationally.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:17.17,英文,,0,0,0,,If each of these is a number from 0 to 255, how many bits does that suggest each number is using?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.17,0:11:19.94,英文,,0,0,0,,Feel free to shout it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.94,0:11:23.86,英文,,0,0,0,,How many bits gives us 256 total possibilities?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.86,0:11:24.54,英文,,0,0,0,,So 8 bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.54,0:11:26.56,英文,,0,0,0,,That should just be sort of a heuristic in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.56,0:11:40.71,英文,,0,0,0,,Anytime you hear something that's in the range of 0 to 255, or 256 values total, think back to week 0, which gives us 8 bits plus another 8 bits, another 8 bits, and another 8 bits, which is to say an IP address typically is 32 bits in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.71,0:11:49.27,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, if we do another bit of quick mental math or think back to week 0, if every IP address is 32 bits, how many computers can we have on the internet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:56.71,英文,,0,0,0,,At once, give or take, roughly 4 billion is the ballpark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.71,0:12:04.85,英文,,0,0,0,,And we don't need to be super precise for discussion's sake, but roughly 4 billion is how high you can account, assuming no negative numbers, if you have 32 bits in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.85,0:12:17.10,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, that's not terribly many numbers of addresses, especially considering the number of humans in the world, the number of us that do have laptops or desktops or devices more generally, phones in our pockets and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.10,0:12:24.14,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me just stipulate for today's purposes that there is even a newer and improved version of IP, otherwise known as version 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.14,0:12:26.73,英文,,0,0,0,,This is version 4, but still super popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.73,0:12:32.25,英文,,0,0,0,,Version 6 uses 128 bits, which is a huge number of possible permutations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.25,0:12:33.95,英文,,0,0,0,,I dare say I can't even pronounce that number.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.95,0:12:34.85,英文,,0,0,0,,It's so big.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.85,0:12:38.31,英文,,0,0,0,,So there are ways around even this limitation already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.31,0:12:41.35,英文,,0,0,0,,So every computer has an address like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.35,0:12:42.63,英文,,0,0,0,,What does that really mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.63,0:12:47.74,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, suppose that I was Phyllis, and the story told visually earlier, and I want to send a message to Brian.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.74,0:12:50.26,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, both Phyllis and Brian have IP addresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.26,0:12:56.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And suppose that Brian's IP address happens to be 1.2.3.4 in that top left-hand corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.15,0:13:07.34,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, Phyllis' Mac or PC or phone would essentially do the equivalent on this human envelope by writing the to address in the middle of the envelope, as is our human convention, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.34,0:13:12.20,英文,,0,0,0,,So this is an envelope, a piece of information, an email, a text message, whatever, destined for Brian.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.20,0:13:15.80,英文,,0,0,0,,And so she would have her computer put Brian's IP address in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.80,0:13:19.45,英文,,0,0,0,,Her IP address is maybe 5.6.7.8.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.45,0:13:29.68,英文,,0,0,0,,So just like our human convention, I might write 5.6.7.8 at the top of the envelope, 5, 6, 7, 8, thereby indicating what the return address is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.68,0:13:35.46,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is helpful because if Brian's computer needs to acknowledge receipt, if he needs to reply in some form,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.46,0:13:38.12,英文,,0,0,0,,And this way, the envelope has all the information we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.12,0:13:46.89,英文,,0,0,0,,But in the real world, servers do a lot of things nowadays, not just email, but maybe chat, maybe video conferencing, maybe any number of other services as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.89,0:13:56.88,英文,,0,0,0,,And so it turns out that an address alone might not be sufficient, because how does Brian's computer know when he opens the envelope, so to speak, that this should be interpreted as an email?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.88,0:14:01.82,英文,,0,0,0,,or interpret it as a chat message or interpret it as a video attachment that Phyllis has sent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.82,0:14:08.83,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, we need some other mechanism, some other hint on this envelope to distinguish one type of internet service from another.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.83,0:14:14.31,英文,,0,0,0,,And so that's where the other acronym in TCPIP comes in, which is TCP.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.31,0:14:23.35,英文,,0,0,0,,So this stands for Transmission Control Protocol, which is just a different set of conventions. that computers adhere to in order to solve a couple of different problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.35,0:14:27.95,英文,,0,0,0,,One is this problem of distinguishing one type of service from another.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.95,0:14:29.13,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.13,0:14:44.92,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, humans decades ago decided, as they started inventing all of these various internet services, the web being the first one, how they might, or the web now being one of the most popular ones, they decided to assign different services that can be used on the internet unique numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.92,0:14:47.36,英文,,0,0,0,,And so two of the most common are these.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.36,0:14:52.87,英文,,0,0,0,,80 is the number that a bunch of humans decided years ago will represent what you and I know as HTTP.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.87,0:14:55.87,英文,,0,0,0,,And we'll talk more technically in a bit about what HTTP is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.87,0:14:59.56,英文,,0,0,0,,But obviously, it's the thing that's in the beginning of every URL nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.56,0:15:03.20,英文,,0,0,0,,Or HTTPS, which, of course, has the S added to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.20,0:15:04.58,英文,,0,0,0,,And that has its own unique number.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.58,0:15:06.86,英文,,0,0,0,,And for now, the S just means secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:11.34,英文,,0,0,0,,One is encrypted or scrambled somehow for privacy's sake, and the other is unencrypted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.34,0:15:13.54,英文,,0,0,0,,It's a little more vulnerable to interception.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.54,0:15:20.21,英文,,0,0,0,,So these two numbers are what the world decided when implementing TCP shall uniquely identify those services.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.21,0:15:21.31,英文,,0,0,0,,So what does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.31,0:15:36.57,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, this means that if Brian's computer in the story from before is hosting not like an email server, but maybe he has a website, and Phyllis is requesting Brian's home page or something like that, she would have her Mac or PC or phone not only write Brian's IP address,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.57,0:15:44.75,英文,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the envelope, but also the number, otherwise known as a port number, that she wants this envelope to be routed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.75,0:15:47.09,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, 80 would be insecure nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:49.77,英文,,0,0,0,,HTTP colon slash slash is sort of passe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.77,0:15:53.66,英文,,0,0,0,,And we almost always see HTTPS colon slash slash now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.66,0:15:55.54,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm just going to go with best practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.54,0:16:01.58,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to add a colon and then the number 443 at the end of Brian's IP address.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.58,0:16:03.84,英文,,0,0,0,,So now I have an IP address for Brian.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.84,0:16:06.46,英文,,0,0,0,,The port number for the service that this is relevant to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.46,0:16:14.65,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm not going to bother writing it, but it turns out that Phyllis's computer would also choose a port number, maybe a random port number, so that Brian can conversely reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.65,0:16:20.83,英文,,0,0,0,,And then the computer can know which response is coming back for which request.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.83,0:16:31.52,英文,,0,0,0,,But the most important one is this one in the To field, whereby this distinguishes this from an email, a chat message, a video conference session, or a Zoom or whatnot from anything else happening on Brian's computer at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.52,0:16:38.39,英文,,0,0,0,,So all this time, if you've seen these terms TCP and IP, those are really two of the most important things that they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.39,0:16:41.51,英文,,0,0,0,,But TCP does one other thing that's super useful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.51,0:16:45.42,英文,,0,0,0,,It turns out that it's super easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.42,0:16:51.74,英文,,0,0,0,,Common, nowadays especially, to transmit a lot of media on the internet, whether it's an image or maybe it's a movie file.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.74,0:17:01.82,英文,,0,0,0,,And it would be a little obnoxious, to say the least, if your downloading a really big file meant that no one else in your dorm room or your household could actually download anything until you're actually done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.82,0:17:07.09,英文,,0,0,0,,So of course, multiple people nowadays can be on the internet at once, even if all of the connections are a little slower.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.09,0:17:09.93,英文,,0,0,0,,But one person's usage does not block someone else's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.93,0:17:11.25,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, how does this work?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.25,0:17:24.43,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, TCP, in conjunction with IP, can also allow you to take a really big image of a cat, which the internet, of course, is filled with, and take a big image of a cat or a big video file of a cat and fragment it into multiple pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.43,0:17:28.99,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm just going to. Sort of roughly tear it down the middle, and then maybe tear it down the middle again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.99,0:17:30.99,英文,,0,0,0,,So now it's four different fragments.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.99,0:17:34.82,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm sorry, but the computer will be reassembling these for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.82,0:17:43.56,英文,,0,0,0,,And what Phyllis's computer could do now, if she's uploading this picture of a cat to Brian's web server, well, she could put one fragment
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.56,0:17:49.10,英文,,0,0,0,,in this envelope, and then have three separate envelopes for the other three fragments.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.10,0:17:53.47,英文,,0,0,0,,And what you could then do on the outside of this envelope is just kind of number them somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.47,0:17:57.69,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, this is something else that TCP and IP together would do for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.69,0:18:07.07,英文,,0,0,0,,This first envelope now might say something like 1, out of four in the memo field, so to speak, of the metaphorical envelope here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.07,0:18:15.72,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, this should be enough information, because now if Brian gets all four of these envelopes, he presumably knows how to reassemble the picture of the cat in order, top to bottom, left to right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.72,0:18:20.58,英文,,0,0,0,,But more importantly, suppose that one of the routers, one of the TFs in the video,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.58,0:18:24.00,英文,,0,0,0,,is sort of distracted and they sort of drop one of the packets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.00,0:18:31.27,英文,,0,0,0,,And that's a metaphor actually in practice for when a router gets really busy, it's got way too much data coming in, it might metaphorically drop packets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.27,0:18:32.67,英文,,0,0,0,,What does that mean in practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.67,0:18:34.83,英文,,0,0,0,,I mean, it literally just ignores the 0's and 1's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.83,0:18:38.15,英文,,0,0,0,,It doesn't save them to its memory because there's just no room left.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.15,0:18:40.33,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's equivalent to sort of dropping the packet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.33,0:18:45.46,英文,,0,0,0,,So suppose now that Brian gets 1 of 4, 3 of 4, and 4 of 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.46,0:18:49.30,英文,,0,0,0,,What can his computer infer now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.30,0:18:55.23,英文,,0,0,0,,After receiving those three packets, 1 of 4, 3 of 4, and 4 of 4, what's the use there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.23,0:18:58.23,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think you're. You're signaling with your fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.23,0:18:58.95,英文,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.95,0:19:00.35,英文,,0,0,0,,Can I call on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.35,0:19:03.19,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so he's missing two out of four, the second of the packets.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.19,0:19:13.19,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is useful now, because you could imagine he can send some message back to Phyllis saying, hey, please retransmit number two of four without having to redownload the entirety of the cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.19,0:19:16.50,英文,,0,0,0,,So there's an efficiency there as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.50,0:19:24.18,英文,,0,0,0,,So TCPIP allows data, really, to go from point A to point B while solving a bunch of these problems along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:32.45,英文,,0,0,0,,So nowadays, if you ever see mention on your Mac or PC of your so-called IP address, that is the sort of problem that's being solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.45,0:19:39.63,英文,,0,0,0,,Questions now on these protocols, these conventions called TCP and IP.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.63,0:19:41.79,英文,,0,0,0,,That's the extent to which we'll need to understand them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.79,0:19:43.11,英文,,0,0,0,,Won't have to implement them, per se.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.11,0:19:46.64,英文,,0,0,0,,We'll just take them hereafter for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.64,0:19:50.48,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions that you've ever been wondering about your home network? Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.61,0:19:59.01,英文,,0,0,0,,A really good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.01,0:20:02.23,英文,,0,0,0,,How does TCP know that a user got a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.23,0:20:11.88,英文,,0,0,0,,Another aspect, another feature of TCP is that Brian's computer, by design of this protocol, will also acknowledge the packets that he's received. And it will do it efficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.88,0:20:20.40,英文,,0,0,0,,If Brian receives all four packets in a pretty narrow window of time, his computer will send to Phyllis's computer a quick message saying, essentially, received all four.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.40,0:20:25.18,英文,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, he'll say the opposite, which is that I'm missing, for instance, two out of four.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.18,0:20:34.62,英文,,0,0,0,,And that just ensures, ultimately, that all of the data is indeed arrived so that you're not missing like a quarter, a quadrant of the cat in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.62,0:20:38.63,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, but that's not the only problem that needs to be solved, ultimately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.63,0:20:43.35,英文,,0,0,0,,We also need to make the internet user friendly, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.35,0:20:51.45,英文,,0,0,0,,And it would be really tedious if you had to visit websites, for instance, by way of their IP addresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.45,0:20:56.59,英文,,0,0,0,,1.2.3.4 is pretty memorable, but there's like 4 billion other possible addresses available.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.59,0:20:59.11,英文,,0,0,0,,And it would be super tedious to remember those.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.11,0:21:02.49,英文,,0,0,0,,It would be bad marketing to advertise those.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.49,0:21:16.40,英文,,0,0,0,,In fact, most of you probably don't even know the phone numbers of your closest friends and family members anymore because you instead store them in your contacts or in your address book associating with numbers that are completely opaque with actual names or strings, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.40,0:21:18.68,英文,,0,0,0,,The same goes for the internet, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.68,0:21:23.50,英文,,0,0,0,,Even though every computer does have and must have a unique IP address numerically, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.50,0:21:24.96,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, routers are computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.96,0:21:27.04,英文,,0,0,0,,Computers just crunch numbers very readily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.04,0:21:29.66,英文,,0,0,0,,But we humans work better with strings of text.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.66,0:21:38.83,英文,,0,0,0,,We need some system for converting user-friendly strings like harvard.edu or yale.edu or google.com to the underlying IP addresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.83,0:21:44.79,英文,,0,0,0,,And that's where the next acronym comes in today, which is DNS, Domain Name System.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.79,0:21:48.41,英文,,0,0,0,,So this is just another technology that's been in use for some time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.41,0:21:57.62,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's a collection of servers on the internet whose purpose in life is to convert domain names to IP addresses, and maybe vice versa as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.62,0:22:03.62,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me stipulate for today's purposes, there are some root DNS servers in the world that, long story short,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.62,0:22:12.50,英文,,0,0,0,,know about all of the dot coms, all of the dot edus, all of the dot, dot, dot, all of the other top-level domains around the world, as well as in the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.50,0:22:21.04,英文,,0,0,0,,And then there are some smaller DNS servers owned by companies, owned by universities, and even in your apartments or homes, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.04,0:22:28.41,英文,,0,0,0,,Indeed, if you have a home router plugged into the wall somewhere, that's not only routing your data in and out of your apartment or home or dorm room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.41,0:22:35.63,英文,,0,0,0,,It's also typically serving as a local, therefore faster, DNS server, a cache, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.63,0:22:44.39,英文,,0,0,0,,It's sort of locally saving your most frequently accessed websites and their IP addresses just to avoid bothering the bigger, more expensive, busier servers all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.39,0:22:46.21,英文,,0,0,0,,So there's DNS servers all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.21,0:22:52.62,英文,,0,0,0,,If you poke around your settings in Windows or Mac OS or Android or iOS, you'll see mention of DNS.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.62,0:22:57.92,英文,,0,0,0,,And you'll probably see the IP addresses of the servers whose purpose in life is to do this conversion for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.92,0:23:05.80,英文,,0,0,0,,But this is a requisite feature if we just want the internet to be user-friendly and allow us to use words instead of numbers alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.80,0:23:07.94,英文,,0,0,0,,What's inside of these DNS servers?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.94,0:23:09.73,英文,,0,0,0,,You know, it's essentially a spreadsheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.73,0:23:15.55,英文,,0,0,0,,Or if we can say it more geekily, it's essentially like a hash table of some sort, which it has keys and values.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.55,0:23:19.75,英文,,0,0,0,,Like the key is the domain name, harvard.edu, yale.edu, google.com.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.75,0:23:27.74,英文,,0,0,0,,And the value is the corresponding IP address, or in many cases, IP addresses, plural, of the corresponding servers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.74,0:23:31.68,英文,,0,0,0,,So here already, even though I've drawn it fairly abstractly, like you would on a chalkboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.68,0:23:38.57,英文,,0,0,0,,It's really probably implemented as some kind of table, maybe a hash table, maybe a database table, maybe SQL or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.57,0:23:41.11,英文,,0,0,0,,Or maybe it's even just a linked list or an array.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.11,0:23:46.66,英文,,0,0,0,,We just have to somehow enable this computer to convert one to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.66,0:23:48.94,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, just to be super precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.94,0:23:59.73,英文,,0,0,0,,DNS servers actually convert what are called fully qualified domain names, which is generally not just harvard.edu, but more verbosely, www.harvard.edu and www.google.com.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.73,0:24:03.95,英文,,0,0,0,,So the whole thing that you would see as a substring of the URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.95,0:24:05.64,英文,,0,0,0,,So that's what DNS does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.64,0:24:10.10,英文,,0,0,0,,And that's what your university, your company, your home router are doing for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.10,0:24:15.42,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me pause here to see if there are any questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.42,0:24:20.62,英文,,0,0,0,,This, too, is just a technology now we'll take for granted, just works.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.62,0:24:23.42,英文,,0,0,0,,Questions at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.42,0:24:24.12,英文,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.12,0:24:34.29,英文,,0,0,0,,So let's now transition among our protocols, really, to the last for today, which will set the stage for actually solving problems with these and writing some code, ultimately, HTTP.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.29,0:24:39.24,英文,,0,0,0,,This is something that you see or hear all day long, even though you rarely have to bother typing it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.24,0:24:47.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Odds are, if you go to harvard.edu, yale.edu, google.com, you don't bother typing HTTP, let alone HTTPS, manually anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.08,0:24:50.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Why? Because your browser autocompletes, that kind of thing, just to make life easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.73,0:24:55.51,英文,,0,0,0,,But it is officially at the beginning of every URL you visit, either HTTP,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.51,0:25:01.27,英文,,0,0,0,,or the more secure HTTPS whenever you're using your browser to access some website.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.27,0:25:06.84,英文,,0,0,0,,So HTTP stands for Hyper Text Transfer Protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.84,0:25:12.64,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's easily one of the most popular, dare say, one of the most powerful features of the internet nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.64,0:25:19.93,英文,,0,0,0,,But the mental model to have here is that HTTP, or the web more generally, is kind of a service that runs on top of the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.93,0:25:25.39,英文,,0,0,0,,And maybe Zoom or Microsoft Teams is another service that runs on top of the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.39,0:25:29.17,英文,,0,0,0,,And iMessage and technologies like it is another service that runs on top of the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.17,0:25:35.80,英文,,0,0,0,,So the internet is really like the lower level plumbing, the TCP IP stuff, the DNS stuff that just gets data from point A to point B.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.80,0:25:44.01,英文,,0,0,0,,But now, and we're in a software development class, ultimately, here in CS50, HTTP is the application-level protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.01,0:25:54.30,英文,,0,0,0,,It's sort of what programmers use, what companies use, what developers use, ultimately, to use the underlying plumbing, to build interesting and powerful things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.30,0:25:56.26,英文,,0,0,0,,So what does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.26,0:26:01.29,英文,,0,0,0,,when it comes to accessing services via HTTP or the more secure HTTPS.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.29,0:26:03.95,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, here is a representative URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.95,0:26:08.34,英文,,0,0,0,,Even though you might not type the whole thing, if you poke around your address bar, this is what's up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.34,0:26:15.06,英文,,0,0,0,,With that said, a lot of browsers nowadays are kind of simplifying, if not dumbing down, what you see with your human eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.06,0:26:17.77,英文,,0,0,0,,just to shorten the strings, especially on mobile devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.77,0:26:21.79,英文,,0,0,0,,But almost always, if you click the URL or highlight it, then you see the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.79,0:26:27.17,英文,,0,0,0,,But on many browsers, you might only ever see example.com, but all of this information is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.17,0:26:31.46,英文,,0,0,0,,It's just getting more and more hidden just for user interfaces' sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.46,0:26:40.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, it turns out when you visit a URL, by default, especially if you type nothing after the .com in this case, you're technically implicitly adding a single slash.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.84,0:26:44.28,英文,,0,0,0,,So a single slash denotes the root of the server.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.28,0:26:47.84,英文,,0,0,0,,That is the default page or folder in the server.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.84,0:26:51.82,英文,,0,0,0,,And the slash, whether or not you type it or not, is implicitly going to be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.82,0:26:53.08,英文,,0,0,0,,And that just means give me the default.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.08,0:26:57.90,英文,,0,0,0,,Whatever's at www.example.com, give me that page or that folder.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.90,0:27:00.26,英文,,0,0,0,,But URLs can be longer than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.26,0:27:04.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And more generally, there can be a path, so to speak. And this is a term of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.15,0:27:09.97,英文,,0,0,0,,A path is some sequence of folder and or file names after a URL like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.97,0:27:15.18,英文,,0,0,0,,And so you might see more specifically that a URL contains a very specific file.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.18,0:27:19.68,英文,,0,0,0,,That's common nowadays anymore, though we will begin today by using this technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.68,0:27:29.44,英文,,0,0,0,,But if there is a file called literally file.html or something else on the server, that file is going to be what this URL pulls up on the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.44,0:27:34.54,英文,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, you might have slash folder slash, which just means show me whatever is inside of this folder.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.54,0:27:41.45,英文,,0,0,0,,Or you might have more verbosely slash folder slash file.html, which will show you that file in that folder.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.45,0:27:47.13,英文,,0,0,0,,And meanwhile, just to give some other terms of art, this is the so-called fully qualified domain name.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.13,0:27:51.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And again, these vocab words don't matter all that much, but you'll hear or see them over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.15,0:27:59.64,英文,,0,0,0,,We generally colloquially just refer to this as the domain name, which is a little less precise, but gets the job done certainly in conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.64,0:28:03.46,英文,,0,0,0,,And this part here I described briefly earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.46,0:28:09.46,英文,,0,0,0,,What's the name for this suffix at the very end of the fully qualified domain name?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.46,0:28:11.53,英文,,0,0,0,,The, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.53,0:28:13.67,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, top-level domain, or TLD.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.67,0:28:16.53,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is just some form of categorization of the URLs.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.53,0:28:19.87,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, the internet got its start within the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.87,0:28:22.03,英文,,0,0,0,,And a lot of the first websites, of course, came from the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.03,0:28:24.91,英文,,0,0,0,,And so for better or for worse, a sort of stake was planted in the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.91,0:28:32.40,英文,,0,0,0,,So generally, .com indicated, at least early on, that it was some kind of commercial enterprise, a business that owned a domain name.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.40,0:28:35.44,英文,,0,0,0,,.edu is an educational institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.44,0:28:37.00,英文,,0,0,0,,.net was some kind of network.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.00,0:28:38.80,英文,,0,0,0,,.gov was the US government.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.80,0:28:45.45,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, there are also country code TLDs, ccTLDs, like .uk or .jp.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.45,0:28:56.22,英文,,0,0,0,,Every country in the world has its own two-letter TLD that might very well be restricted to only servers or companies or people in that country.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.22,0:28:58.14,英文,,0,0,0,,Many of them can be used by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.14,0:29:02.52,英文,,0,0,0,,You've used a lot of URLs in this class, ending in cs50.io.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.52,0:29:05.06,英文,,0,0,0,,That doesn't mean input-output.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.06,0:29:13.34,英文,,0,0,0,,It actually is a TLD from another country that lets anyone on the internet pay for, and on an annual basis, using that domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.34,0:29:17.86,英文,,0,0,0,,.tv, for instance, you might see in some cases, like twitch.tv and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.86,0:29:24.66,英文,,0,0,0,,That, too, is owned by another country that allows others in the English-speaking world, in this case, to use it as though it connotes TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.66,0:29:29.53,英文,,0,0,0,,Those are just different types of TLDs that roughly categorize where the domain lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.53,0:29:31.89,英文,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't necessarily mean it's commercial anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.89,0:29:35.19,英文,,0,0,0,,It doesn't necessarily mean it's a network anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.19,0:29:42.94,英文,,0,0,0,,For the most part, there are hundreds of TLDs now, for better or for worse, most of which are less common than these big ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.94,0:29:50.68,英文,,0,0,0,,But most anyone can buy most of them with just some restrictions on things like .edu and .gov that are still very much regulated.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.68,0:29:54.36,英文,,0,0,0,,This, meanwhile, is what we might call the hostname, www.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.36,0:29:56.69,英文,,0,0,0,,It's obviously a super common convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.69,0:30:00.35,英文,,0,0,0,,Like, almost every website uses www as its hostname.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.35,0:30:01.63,英文,,0,0,0,,But that's a human convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.63,0:30:02.99,英文,,0,0,0,,It's not a requirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.99,0:30:05.61,英文,,0,0,0,,And indeed, some websites don't even bother having a hostname.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.61,0:30:09.92,英文,,0,0,0,,They just use their domain to advertise their website.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.92,0:30:13.04,英文,,0,0,0,,This now is going to be the scheme or the protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.04,0:30:23.25,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is just going to indicate via what protocol the computer, your Mac, your PC, your phone, should use when accessing content at that address.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.25,0:30:25.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Because indeed, there are other protocols you can use.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.73,0:30:32.11,英文,,0,0,0,,But for the most part, we'll only focus on HTTP or equivalently HTTPS.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.11,0:30:32.81,英文,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.81,0:30:40.94,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions now on those just definitions, building blocks of URLs, just so we all sort of share a common vocabulary?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.94,0:30:42.24,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.24,0:30:46.18,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.18,0:30:46.42,英文,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.42,0:30:48.34,英文,,0,0,0,,We'll come back to this, actually, later today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.34,0:30:56.61,英文,,0,0,0,,There's a technical term known as local host, which is a generic name for your computer, your Mac, your PC, your phone, especially when you're doing software development.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.61,0:31:10.56,英文,,0,0,0,,And by convention, your own computer has not only whatever IP address you get from your university or your internet service provider, it also has a reflexive IP address, one that just always refers to itself, which is 127.0.0.1.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.56,0:31:11.80,英文,,0,0,0,,And that's just a human convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.80,0:31:14.78,英文,,0,0,0,,Humans decided that shall refer always to your computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.78,0:31:20.78,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's actually going to be useful today and onward, because we can use that when doing development on our own computers, ultimately.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.78,0:31:27.79,英文,,0,0,0,,Other questions on URLs, IP, DNS, or any of these building blocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.79,0:31:32.30,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so what do we mean by HTTP being a protocol?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.30,0:31:38.76,英文,,0,0,0,,When I extended my hand earlier as a human handshake, a typical human in healthy times would know to respond in turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.76,0:31:44.74,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, how does Brian's computer know to respond to Phyllis' envelope, whatever message is therein?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.74,0:31:51.40,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, assuming that Brian is indeed still a web server in the story, and Phyllis was trying to upload a cat or maybe download a cat,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.40,0:31:58.03,英文,,0,0,0,,From Brian's web server, inside of Phyllis's envelope would have been a message, literally in text.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.03,0:32:00.17,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's English, for the most part.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.17,0:32:14.01,英文,,0,0,0,,And it would contain, at the beginning of that message, literally one of these English verbs, either get, which means just that, get me the home page, get me a picture of a cat, get me a picture of a dog, or a video, or anything else, or post, which often means
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.01,0:32:21.13,英文,,0,0,0,,Post, that is, upload a picture of a cat or a dog or something else to the server instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.13,0:32:31.38,英文,,0,0,0,,That's not strictly the only use cases for these, but you can generally think of them as one is just getting information and the other is posting from the client, from Phyllis to the server, in this case, Brian.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.38,0:32:33.52,英文,,0,0,0,,So those are the two keywords that we might see.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.52,0:32:40.01,英文,,0,0,0,,And why is this useful? Well, it turns out we can start to see in our own Mac or PC Some of these very same messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.01,0:32:53.34,英文,,0,0,0,,For instance, if Phyllis were visiting not Brian's but example.com, that web server, inside of her metaphorical envelope, there would be a textual message that literally starts with get slash
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.34,0:32:55.30,英文,,0,0,0,,Then the word HTTP.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.30,0:32:56.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Then the version she's using.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.84,0:32:58.46,英文,,0,0,0,,1.1 is very common.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.46,0:33:00.10,英文,,0,0,0,,2 and 3 are becoming more common.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.10,0:33:02.38,英文,,0,0,0,,But HTTP generally looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.38,0:33:12.31,英文,,0,0,0,,The next line of text in her envelope would probably say host colon, then literally the fully qualified domain name of the server she's accessing, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.31,0:33:15.21,英文,,0,0,0,,And this happens super commonly, especially on small websites.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.21,0:33:22.23,英文,,0,0,0,,If one server is hosting multiple domain names, multiple websites, this just distinguishes which one she actually wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.23,0:33:25.66,英文,,0,0,0,,And then there's usually a whole bunch of other lines of text as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.66,0:33:28.48,英文,,0,0,0,,So where can you actually see this?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.48,0:33:31.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, let me actually go ahead and do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.84,0:33:32.86,英文,,0,0,0,,Give me just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.86,0:33:35.64,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to open up on my computer here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.64,0:33:38.12,英文,,0,0,0,,An empty Chrome window in incognito mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.12,0:33:43.78,英文,,0,0,0,,Generally speaking, incognito mode or private mode is used when you don't want there to be left remnants of what websites you visited.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.78,0:33:51.51,英文,,0,0,0,,And it has the effect for software developers of just forgetting any things you might have tried already within your browser, including things called cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.51,0:33:54.77,英文,,0,0,0,,More on those another time. Your autocomplete history and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.77,0:34:02.91,英文,,0,0,0,,So for development purposes, incognito mode is especially helpful, because it's sort of like starting with a clean slate every time you open a new private or incognito mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.91,0:34:07.75,英文,,0,0,0,,So there's not going to be any remnants of previous testing or code that you've been playing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.75,0:34:11.79,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to go ahead and do this. I'm going to go ahead and right-click.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.79,0:34:15.12,英文,,0,0,0,,Or Control-click on Chrome. I'm going to choose Inspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.12,0:34:19.08,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's going to pull up this window, sometimes on the side, sometimes on the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.08,0:34:22.14,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to move it to the bottom just so we can see it a little more readily.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.14,0:34:23.40,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to zoom in.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.40,0:34:26.23,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's going to look a little arcane at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.23,0:34:28.41,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to just highlight a few of these tabs.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.41,0:34:34.77,英文,,0,0,0,,We'll see here along the top that there's Elements, Console, Sources, Network, and a whole bunch of other things as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.77,0:34:36.84,英文,,0,0,0,,This is sort of the advanced mode in Chrome.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.84,0:34:40.68,英文,,0,0,0,,And Safari and Firefox and Edge have their own equivalents of these features.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.68,0:34:45.04,英文,,0,0,0,,They've always been there, even if you've never clicked the right button to enable these features.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.04,0:34:47.82,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to focus for a moment on network, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.82,0:34:57.59,英文,,0,0,0,,This is a feature of the browser that's going to allow me, the programmer in this case, or the engineer, to just kind of look at what messages my browser is actually sending to a server.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.59,0:35:00.27,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me go ahead and do something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.27,0:35:02.70,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.70,0:35:15.86,英文,,0,0,0,,For instance, in my browser here, and I'm going to shrink the window just a little bit so we can see it exactly, I'm going to visit https://www.harvard.edu.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.86,0:35:21.82,英文,,0,0,0,,And now I'm going to hit Enter. And a whole bunch of stuff just happened along the bottom of my screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.82,0:35:26.54,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to try to pull my window up just a little bit so we can focus on a subset of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.54,0:35:33.17,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me pull this up, covering up really the content of the page, focusing on these lower-level details down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.17,0:35:39.78,英文,,0,0,0,,And what I want to see first is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.78,0:35:45.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and reload this page here after retaining the log so that we can see absolutely everything on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.84,0:35:51.63,英文,,0,0,0,,And to be clear, I just checked, because I forgot earlier, preserve log, because I wanted to preserve everything on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.63,0:35:53.41,英文,,0,0,0,,I want to see everything all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.41,0:35:54.47,英文,,0,0,0,,And we'll see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.47,0:35:59.31,英文,,0,0,0,,The very first line of output is completely overwhelming with detail at first glance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.31,0:36:02.51,英文,,0,0,0,,But what you'll see here, if I start to scroll down,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.51,0:36:06.44,英文,,0,0,0,,And down and down and down are the so-called request headers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.44,0:36:07.98,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me zoom in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.98,0:36:21.74,英文,,0,0,0,,And what you're seeing inside of Chrome, inside of its Network tab, in its so-called Developer Tools, again, this is just for engineering types, you'll see all of the headers, all of the lines of text that magically were sent by my Mac
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.74,0:36:29.76,英文,,0,0,0,,to Harvard.edu, much like from Phyllis to Brian's server in that story, so I can see exactly what messengers are being sent.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.76,0:36:37.52,英文,,0,0,0,,And a lot of this we haven't talked about yet, but we do see some mention of get, and we see some mention of slash, and a bunch of other arcane details.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.52,0:36:42.14,英文,,0,0,0,,But notice, they're all sort of key value pairs, with the colon here indicating
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.14,0:36:43.72,英文,,0,0,0,,What the corresponding value is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.72,0:36:45.37,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, most of this is not going to be interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.37,0:36:48.03,英文,,0,0,0,,And we're not going to focus too much on the weeds of all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.03,0:36:53.00,英文,,0,0,0,,But it indeed gives us a sense of what's inside of that virtual envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.00,0:36:54.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, harvard.edu is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.84,0:36:58.76,英文,,0,0,0,,But there's other websites we might visit as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.76,0:37:03.51,英文,,0,0,0,,And no matter what they are, we're going to expect, ultimately, an HTTP response.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.51,0:37:16.70,英文,,0,0,0,,So in addition to a computer, like my Mac or Phyllis's computer, sending a request containing gets and host and those details, too, you'll see here in my slide form just representative response from the server.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.70,0:37:21.86,英文,,0,0,0,,And notice that key here is that the server is responding in the same version of HTTP in this example.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.86,0:37:28.00,英文,,0,0,0,,It's sending back this so-called status code, just a numeric code that indicates, in this case, that everything's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.00,0:37:37.73,英文,,0,0,0,,And it includes this header, this HTTP header, which, again, is just a key value pair saying that the type of this content that's coming back from the server is text slash HTML.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.73,0:37:39.83,英文,,0,0,0,,More on HTML in just a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.83,0:37:44.76,英文,,0,0,0,,But for our purposes now, this just means that harvard.edu is sending me back a web page.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.76,0:37:52.20,英文,,0,0,0,,And indeed, if we hide all of this technical stuff, that's the web page that we saw up here with all of the usual imagery and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.20,0:37:59.19,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, I can see this if I scroll back up, not to request headers, but response headers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.19,0:38:07.29,英文,,0,0,0,,You'll see up here that we get back responses, including the date that the server responded and a whole bunch of other details as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.29,0:38:09.73,英文,,0,0,0,,And honestly, this has always been under your fingertips.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.73,0:38:13.87,英文,,0,0,0,,And it will soon be useful as we start making web-based applications ultimately.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.87,0:38:16.19,英文,,0,0,0,,But this very quickly gets overwhelming quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.19,0:38:21.53,英文,,0,0,0,,And so better than this might actually be a tool that we can use within our code space itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.53,0:38:23.67,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me go back to VS Code here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.67,0:38:25.02,英文,,0,0,0,,I didn't open any code tabs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.02,0:38:27.18,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to use my terminal window for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.18,0:38:34.29,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to run a couple of commands that are going to allow me to actually see what is going on when I request one website.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.29,0:38:36.89,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and use a command called curl.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.89,0:38:38.35,英文,,0,0,0,,for connect URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.35,0:38:42.89,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is like a command line, black and white program, that's going to pretend to be a browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.89,0:38:45.72,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's going to connect to the URL, show me the headers.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.72,0:38:51.40,英文,,0,0,0,,But it's not going to show me the images or the graphics, which might very well be useful to the humans, but not to me right now as the developer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.40,0:38:52.58,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to do curl.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.58,0:39:03.65,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to do dash i. And then I'm going to do HTTPS colon slash slash www.harvard.edu slash, as though I'm pretending to be a browser requesting the home page.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.65,0:39:15.09,英文,,0,0,0,,And what's nice about curl is, albeit overwhelming, too, you'll get back a whole response from the server containing only those header values, the key value pairs inside of the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.09,0:39:16.93,英文,,0,0,0,,And we'll ignore almost all of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.93,0:39:18.65,英文,,0,0,0,,But here is the response from the server.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.65,0:39:23.09,英文,,0,0,0,,It responded using a new and improved version of HTTP, in this case, version 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.09,0:39:25.12,英文,,0,0,0,,And it gave me back a 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.12,0:39:27.94,英文,,0,0,0,,There's my content type, text slash HTML.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.94,0:39:32.96,英文,,0,0,0,,And then this char set happens to do with the encoding, if it's Unicode or ASCII or something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.96,0:39:35.84,英文,,0,0,0,,And then there's all this other overwhelming detail for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.84,0:39:40.88,英文,,0,0,0,,But this is the beginnings of my ability to just kind of poke around and see how the server works.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.88,0:39:46.76,英文,,0,0,0,,And it turns out, too, that we'll be able to see other potential responses as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.76,0:39:52.25,英文,,0,0,0,,So for instance, HTTP might not only return 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.25,0:39:53.79,英文,,0,0,0,,What if I do this instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.79,0:40:01.91,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and visit curl-i http://www.harvard.edu.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.91,0:40:05.12,英文,,0,0,0,,So notice I deliberately use the insecure version of the URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.12,0:40:09.58,英文,,0,0,0,,which maybe Harvard's system administration doesn't like anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.58,0:40:17.93,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, how can they ensure that I, the end user, the student, nonetheless use HTTPS, even if I didn't type it myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.93,0:40:22.35,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, let me run just that command with just HTTP, not HTTPS.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.35,0:40:24.41,英文,,0,0,0,,And you'll see that everything is not OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.41,0:40:26.38,英文,,0,0,0,,It didn't come back with a 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.38,0:40:30.44,英文,,0,0,0,,It came back with 301 in this message saying, Harvard moved permanently.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.44,0:40:33.04,英文,,0,0,0,,But here's where you can look for another clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.04,0:40:43.27,英文,,0,0,0,,Among all of these lines, most of which I don't care about, there's a location header, colon, that's a little hint to me that says where Harvard University has apparently moved to on the web.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.27,0:40:47.13,英文,,0,0,0,,And what's different about this URL, just to be clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.13,0:40:48.79,英文,,0,0,0,,It has the S included.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.79,0:40:59.77,英文,,0,0,0,,And what your browser will do by default, because Google and Microsoft and Mozilla programmed it this way, whenever it sees a 301 response instead of 200, it won't show you any web page.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.77,0:41:06.37,英文,,0,0,0,,It will look for a location header, find that URL, and then automatically, quote unquote, redirect you there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.37,0:41:09.41,英文,,0,0,0,,So this is why it doesn't matter what we type in the browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.41,0:41:16.94,英文,,0,0,0,,Harvard can have its servers send these semi-secret messages to our browsers, and then it will just visit a second URL all automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.94,0:41:19.66,英文,,0,0,0,,And you can do this with host names as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.66,0:41:24.36,英文,,0,0,0,,Suppose that Harvard does not want to standardize on harvard.edu.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.36,0:41:24.70,英文,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.70,0:41:32.12,英文,,0,0,0,,They just want it to always be www. Maybe it's a branding thing. Maybe it's a technical thing. We can see the exact same response here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.12,0:41:41.41,英文,,0,0,0,,This first tells me, when I visit HTTP, harvard.edu with no www, Harvard minimally wants me to be using a secure connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.41,0:41:43.74,英文,,0,0,0,,If I then, OK, fine, cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.74,0:41:45.72,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and clear my screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.72,0:41:48.28,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me add the S, but not the www.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.28,0:41:51.87,英文,,0,0,0,,You can see here that it again responded with a 301.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.87,0:41:55.51,英文,,0,0,0,,up here, and the location now adds the www.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.51,0:41:59.17,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's just a way of bouncing users from one place to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.17,0:42:09.39,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is all thanks to HTTP boiling down to relatively simple messages inside of the envelope that tell the computer, the browser in this case,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.39,0:42:10.87,英文,,0,0,0,,How to respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.87,0:42:18.68,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, odds are you've seen others besides 301, even though you've probably never seen that actual number, unless you've done this kind of thing before.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.68,0:42:24.62,英文,,0,0,0,,But there probably is a number that everyone in this room has seen, even if you've never really wondered, why is it that number?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.62,0:42:27.65,英文,,0,0,0,,I think you're smiling. What number are you thinking of?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.65,0:42:29.21,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so 404.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.21,0:42:30.35,英文,,0,0,0,,Why is 404?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.35,0:42:33.65,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, 404 indicates, by convention, not found.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.65,0:42:41.78,英文,,0,0,0,,And now why the world decided years ago to show us normal humans on the internet 404 is anything significant is unclear.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.78,0:42:42.94,英文,,0,0,0,,That's sort of like bad design.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.94,0:42:46.00,英文,,0,0,0,,Like, what do I care if the status code is 404?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.00,0:42:49.36,英文,,0,0,0,,But it's common enough on the internet that probably all of us have seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.36,0:42:56.30,英文,,0,0,0,,But that just means that some server, when you visit a URL that's incorrect, maybe it's outdated, the URL has been changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.30,0:43:08.95,英文,,0,0,0,,If you see a 404, it just means that the virtual envelope that came from the server back to your Mac or PC or phone contains not 200 OK, not 301 moved permanently, but 404 not found instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.95,0:43:15.67,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's usually accompanied by a technical message, maybe a cute picture of a cat sort of hiding because it means not found, or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.67,0:43:20.03,英文,,0,0,0,,The aesthetics are entirely up to the server, but that's what the 404 means.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.03,0:43:28.22,英文,,0,0,0,,And there's other codes, too, a few of which you'll use in the coming weeks as we transition from command line programs in C and Python to web-based ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.22,0:43:34.66,英文,,0,0,0,,We've seen a few of these already, and several of them are kind of variants of the same thing, like these 300 ones here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.66,0:43:42.86,英文,,0,0,0,,But we'll see others, like 403 forbidden means you probably forgot to log in or you need to log in or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.86,0:43:44.93,英文,,0,0,0,,Internal server error, right now, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.93,0:43:48.41,英文,,0,0,0,,In the coming weeks, you will absolutely encounter 500 errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.41,0:43:50.13,英文,,0,0,0,,And they're always your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.13,0:43:57.35,英文,,0,0,0,,It's going to be the equivalent of a segmentation fault in C. A 500 error means you or I screwed up when writing some code.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.35,0:44:00.63,英文,,0,0,0,,So we're going to see that. But it's just going to be an opportunity for us to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.63,0:44:09.07,英文,,0,0,0,,If a server is overloaded, you often see 503, like something's unavailable because something's too popular or is maybe worse, getting attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.07,0:44:11.13,英文,,0,0,0,,This is an old example.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.13,0:44:19.92,英文,,0,0,0,,April Fool's joke, 418 is not actually used in practice, but someone took the time to write up an entire formal technical proposal so that servers can respond saying, I am a teapot.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.92,0:44:24.72,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's kind of part of internet lore, and there's other ones of these status codes as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.72,0:44:35.08,英文,,0,0,0,,But this is useful because eventually we'll see in code you can use this understanding, high level as it might be of HTTP, to do some interesting and powerful things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.08,0:44:36.75,英文,,0,0,0,,So for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.75,0:44:40.05,英文,,0,0,0,,We can even send fancier URLs to servers.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.05,0:45:02.04,英文,,0,0,0,,It turns out, as we'll soon see, if you send a message like this, get slash search question mark q equals cat, and then HTTP 1.1 or whatever version, and you send that message to Google's server, www.google.com, this is how you can specify not just the path of a web page that you want, slash search in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.04,0:45:12.37,英文,,0,0,0,,The question mark, it turns out, is going to be a convention in the internet, in the web specifically, for passing user input to the server as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.37,0:45:17.13,英文,,0,0,0,,In fact, you've probably never paid close attention to URLs, but they very often have question marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.13,0:45:18.93,英文,,0,0,0,,They very often have equal signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.93,0:45:24.42,英文,,0,0,0,,And indeed, even google.com supports a certain key, Q in this case, for query.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.42,0:45:28.80,英文,,0,0,0,,And you can put anything you want after that in order to search for actual cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.80,0:45:33.00,英文,,0,0,0,,So if I actually go back to Chrome itself here for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.00,0:45:37.02,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me pull back open my Chrome browser here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.02,0:45:41.04,英文,,0,0,0,,Previously, I was using incognito mode for harvard.edu.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.04,0:45:45.20,英文,,0,0,0,,I've gone ahead and closed that window and opened a new one so we can start fresh by visiting Google.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.20,0:45:49.07,英文,,0,0,0,,Normally, you and I are in the habit of going to google.com and searching via the form.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.07,0:45:55.97,英文,,0,0,0,,Or nowadays, you just type your search query in the browser itself, and it brings you automatically to Google or Bing or something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.97,0:45:57.45,英文,,0,0,0,,But I can really be pedantic here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.45,0:45:58.89,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and zoom in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.89,0:46:04.72,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'll manually go to HTTPS colon slash slash www.google.com slash search.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.72,0:46:08.20,英文,,0,0,0,,Question mark q equals maybe cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.20,0:46:13.17,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, this would not be a very user-friendly experience if all of us had to manually type out something crazy like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.17,0:46:20.43,英文,,0,0,0,,But that's what the form is redirecting you to when you type in more user-friendly cats into a text box.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.43,0:46:25.60,英文,,0,0,0,,If I hit Enter here, we'll get back, indeed, a whole bunch of search results about cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.60,0:46:30.48,英文,,0,0,0,,If I zoom back in, and maybe I change it from cats to dogs, that too is going to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.48,0:46:37.21,英文,,0,0,0,,And notice it's pre-populating the text box, because Google has written its code in order to do so as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.21,0:46:51.49,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, apropos of the video with which we began today from yesteryear, one of the better Yale pranks over the years, has anyone actually ever been to safetyschool.org?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.49,0:46:55.54,英文,,0,0,0,,And to our friends at Yale watching live, hi, safetyschool.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.54,0:47:00.64,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's kind of fun if you actually visit it, depending on who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.64,0:47:10.80,英文,,0,0,0,,So if I open up a new window here, and I go to http://safetyschool.org, zooming in, Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.80,0:47:12.82,英文,,0,0,0,,My, oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.82,0:47:14.34,英文,,0,0,0,,Look at where it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.34,0:47:16.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, how does that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.08,0:47:16.48,英文,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.48,0:47:20.74,英文,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.74,0:47:22.26,英文,,0,0,0,,This is not a CS50 thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.26,0:47:31.27,英文,,0,0,0,,Someone out there who I don't know who they are for like 20 years has been paying annually for that domain, safetyschool.org, for just this joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.27,0:47:42.72,英文,,0,0,0,,But if I now go back into VS Code here in my terminal window, and a little more sophisticatedly, let me do curl dash i HTTP colon slash slash SafetySchool.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.72,0:47:45.42,英文,,0,0,0,,The browser, of course, immediately redirected me to the website.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.42,0:47:47.18,英文,,0,0,0,,But what's going on underneath the hood?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.18,0:47:53.23,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, 20-some years ago, someone bought the domain, configured the server, quite simply to spit this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.23,0:48:00.16,英文,,0,0,0,,SafetySchool.org, for years, has moved permanently to www.yale.edu.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.16,0:48:04.80,英文,,0,0,0,,So just a little demonstration of what you can do with just a little bit of understanding of HTTP.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.80,0:48:05.78,英文,,0,0,0,,That's been a lot already.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.78,0:48:08.30,英文,,0,0,0,,We've laid the foundation for understanding how the internet works.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.30,0:48:17.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to use it with a language called HTML, Hypertext Markup Language, CSS, Cascading Style Sheets, and JavaScript, a proper programming language.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.08,0:48:19.25,英文,,0,0,0,,But first, it feels opportune to take a 10-minute break.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.25,0:48:25.75,英文,,0,0,0,,We have some wonderful Halloween candy in the transept, and we'll be back in 10 with those languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.75,0:48:26.73,英文,,0,0,0,,We're headed up to Boston.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.79,0:48:33.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Checking out the stadium for the prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.73,0:48:36.41,英文,,0,0,0,,A few years ago, I was at a math conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.41,0:48:41.16,英文,,0,0,0,,And I was sitting around at the table at dinner with a few other mathematicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.16,0:48:49.84,英文,,0,0,0,,And one of them went to Harvard and started telling the story of this amazing prank that was against Harvard.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.84,0:48:55.62,英文,,0,0,0,,And at that point, I felt I had to interrupt and said, well, actually, I can tell you a lot more about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.45,0:48:59.73,英文,,0,0,0,,The idea was perfected in a dorm room.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.73,0:49:03.85,英文,,0,0,0,,We came up with the idea, actually, to prank them with signs at the football game.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.85,0:49:07.50,英文,,0,0,0,,We threw some ideas out there as far as what the signs would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.50,0:49:10.14,英文,,0,0,0,,We eventually settled on, we suck.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.14,0:49:13.24,英文,,0,0,0,,And my immediate reaction was, no, this will never work.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.24,0:49:20.00,英文,,0,0,0,,However, the problem solver in me started thinking, well, maybe we can make this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.00,0:49:20.42,英文,,0,0,0,,Problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.36,0:49:33.71,英文,,0,0,0,,They had to infiltrate Harvard Stadium without getting caught, sneak in 1,800 placards, distribute them to unsuspecting Harvard fans, and then convince those fans to prank themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.71,0:49:40.52,英文,,0,0,0,,We thought about basically every possible thing that could go wrong and tried to come up with a solution for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.37,0:49:51.68,英文,,0,0,0,,They made fake Harvard IDs and fake backstories, fake placard designs, and a 28-member fake pep squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.68,0:49:58.26,英文,,0,0,0,,On November 20, 2004, the fake Harvard students smuggled the placards into the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.05,0:50:26.58,英文,,0,0,0,,But then, trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.58,0:50:32.96,英文,,0,0,0,,I just showed him the front of this ID and all of a sudden he just ran away and he felt so embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.96,0:50:37.06,英文,,0,0,0,,Having escaped one confrontation, they couldn't risk another.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.06,0:50:39.04,英文,,0,0,0,,It was time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.04,0:50:40.32,英文,,0,0,0,,This just looks like a total mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.39,0:50:44.35,英文,,0,0,0,,We have absolutely no idea if this is going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.35,0:50:46.42,英文,,0,0,0,,What was once a prank became a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.07,0:51:06.67,英文,,0,0,0,,And immediately we started hearing chants from the other side, You suck!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.67,0:51:09.37,英文,,0,0,0,,You suck!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.37,0:51:12.39,英文,,0,0,0,,And I think it was at that point in time that we knew we had pulled it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.39,0:51:13.63,英文,,0,0,0,,There it goes again!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.72,0:51:25.60,英文,,0,0,0,,I really think it didn't matter that Harvard won because of the prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.60,0:51:29.75,英文,,0,0,0,,For a lot of Yale students and alumni, we definitely won that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.72,0:51:54.13,英文,,0,0,0,,Thank you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.13,0:51:55.39,英文,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.39,0:51:56.51,英文,,0,0,0,,Oh, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.51,0:51:57.55,英文,,0,0,0,,Oh, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.55,0:51:59.75,英文,,0,0,0,,A little Halloween candy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.75,0:52:00.99,英文,,0,0,0,,Thank you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.99,0:52:04.68,英文,,0,0,0,,So glad I wore the same thing today.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.68,0:52:10.76,英文,,0,0,0,,So in just a moment, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.76,0:52:18.55,英文,,0,0,0,,OK, so in just a moment, we'll transition to understanding all the more now what we can do with this underlying infrastructure.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.55,0:52:25.81,英文,,0,0,0,,So again, HTTP and below it, TCP, IP is all about just getting the data from point A to point B in some standardized way.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.81,0:52:27.35,英文,,0,0,0,,But now let's talk about HTML.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.35,0:52:32.72,英文,,0,0,0,,This is the language in which web pages themselves are written, hypertext markup language.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.72,0:52:35.56,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, some of you might have used this before to make personal home pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.56,0:52:39.30,英文,,0,0,0,,Some of you might have dabbled, even if using some website to create your own home page.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.30,0:52:47.31,英文,,0,0,0,,But understanding this language is useful, certainly for creating the aesthetics of a web page, conveying data that's of interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.31,0:52:53.44,英文,,0,0,0,,But at the end of the day, it and the language we'll look at next, CSS, are not programming languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.44,0:52:57.62,英文,,0,0,0,,There's going to be no functions, no loops, no programming logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.62,0:53:06.79,英文,,0,0,0,,But we will end today with a teaser of a proper programming language called JavaScript via which you can manipulate all of these various other languages as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.79,0:53:08.99,英文,,0,0,0,,So ultimately, HTML has two features.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.99,0:53:21.20,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is a language that we spend very brief amount of time on because it really boils down to just a couple of basic ideas and then vocabulary that you'll build out over time just by googling, looking up references, looking at other pages, source code.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.20,0:53:25.54,英文,,0,0,0,,But tags and attributes are what characterize HTML. Now, what do I mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.54,0:53:37.60,英文,,0,0,0,,Here, for instance, is the HTML code via which you can make probably the simplest of all web pages, one that quite simply says in the browser window, hello, title, and hello, body, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.60,0:53:39.18,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, what does this actually mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.18,0:53:41.34,英文,,0,0,0,,If you imagine opening up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.34,0:53:47.12,英文,,0,0,0,,This code, in a browser, be it on a Mac or PC or phone, you'll see typically some kind of rectangular window.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.12,0:53:49.93,英文,,0,0,0,,And there's usually a tab that has the title of that page.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.93,0:53:53.11,英文,,0,0,0,,And then most of the rectangular region is the web page itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.11,0:53:58.79,英文,,0,0,0,,What you're looking at, then, is the code that's going to put hello title in the title bar in the tab at the very top.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.79,0:54:06.35,英文,,0,0,0,,And down at the bottom, hello body is going to be all that's in the big black and white box that composes the rest of the browser window itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.35,0:54:09.65,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, what are the salient characteristics here that we'll now start to take for granted?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.65,0:54:11.27,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, first, whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.27,0:54:19.08,英文,,0,0,0,,First, let's go ahead and give me just a moment here and actually do something with this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.08,0:54:20.38,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to go ahead and do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.38,0:54:26.27,英文,,0,0,0,,Back in VS Code here, I'm going to first create a file called, say, hello.html.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.27,0:54:30.49,英文,,0,0,0,,And in this tab, I'm going to go ahead and really repeat exactly that same code.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.49,0:54:33.30,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, I had this line first, doctype HTML.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.30,0:54:43.32,英文,,0,0,0,,Then I had this line, HTML lang equals quote, unquote, EN, close quote. Then I had inside of that head. Then I had inside of that title. Then inside of that, I had hello, title.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.32,0:54:47.26,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm doing this quickly, because we'll tease apart in a moment what it actually all means.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.26,0:54:53.27,英文,,0,0,0,,And then down here, below that so-called head, I had just the text, hello, body.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.27,0:54:57.07,英文,,0,0,0,,So at the moment, that, I claim, is the entirety of a web page.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.07,0:55:02.23,英文,,0,0,0,,But it currently lives in my code space, so to speak, in a file called hello.html.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.23,0:55:04.09,英文,,0,0,0,,That's fine if I want to create it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.09,0:55:07.61,英文,,0,0,0,,But how do I, how do you, how does anyone on the internet actually view it?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.61,0:55:11.42,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, to serve a web page, you indeed need a web server.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.42,0:55:17.82,英文,,0,0,0,,And it turns out that Codespaces comes with one of these pre-installed, because we, CS50 staff, did so for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.82,0:55:28.65,英文,,0,0,0,,And what you can do in a terminal window, once you have an HTML file ready to go that you want the world to see, you can literally run in your terminal window HTTP dash server.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.65,0:55:29.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Single command.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.73,0:55:33.84,英文,,0,0,0,,And what that's going to do for you is start a web server, that is to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.84,0:55:37.32,英文,,0,0,0,,A program whose purpose in life is just to serve web pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.32,0:55:46.39,英文,,0,0,0,,And even though probably up until now, for years, you probably, if you're like me, equate server, quote unquote, with a physical device, server is really a piece of software.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.39,0:55:48.79,英文,,0,0,0,,It just tends to run on big, fancy devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.79,0:55:54.22,英文,,0,0,0,,So when we say server, we often all think of, in our mind's eye, big, expensive devices, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.22,0:56:00.09,英文,,0,0,0,,But a server is just a program whose purpose in life is to respond to requests with responses.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.09,0:56:01.79,英文,,0,0,0,,And that's the vernacular there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.79,0:56:09.60,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, once you run HTTP server, and I'm going to do a bit of magic because I set this up before class just to make sure it goes smoothly, you'll see some output like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.60,0:56:14.81,英文,,0,0,0,,whereby your server is now available on a very long URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.81,0:56:19.09,英文,,0,0,0,,Mine here is a very long URL that will be different from yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.09,0:56:29.68,英文,,0,0,0,,But what this is is a unique identifier that your code space has temporarily generated so that you can now access, and ideally only you can access, that file using your browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.68,0:56:37.70,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, if I flip the URL or you flip the URL to public by right-clicking or control-clicking the right features of VS Code, you can enable anyone in the world to visit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.70,0:56:44.99,英文,,0,0,0,,But we're not going to ultimately host our websites in your code space, because as soon as you log off for the night and the thing shuts down, the website will go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.99,0:56:54.91,英文,,0,0,0,,But at the end of the semester, particularly for final projects, we'll show you ways that you can put your own website, your own code, on the actual internet 24-7, 365,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.91,0:57:02.91,英文,,0,0,0,,even with your own domain name if you want to get one, so that it lives independent of your own sleep schedule and usage schedule of VS Code here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.91,0:57:05.58,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to go ahead now and visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.58,0:57:08.76,英文,,0,0,0,,This URL in another tab of my browser.
