Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.75,1:00:00.29,英文,,0,0,0,,So indeed, this lecture, this class, has been evolving over time, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.29,1:00:03.97,英文,,0,0,0,,So let's now focus on the next line, as well as the bottom line.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.97,1:00:06.47,英文,,0,0,0,,And you'll notice some deliberate symmetry here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.47,1:00:08.93,英文,,0,0,0,,This here is what we're going to call a tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.93,1:00:10.39,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's technically different from this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.39,1:00:11.76,英文,,0,0,0,,This is a document type declaration.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.76,1:00:13.06,英文,,0,0,0,,It's got the weird exclamation point.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.06,1:00:14.20,英文,,0,0,0,,That's the only anomaly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.20,1:00:16.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Everything else follows a pattern.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.08,1:00:19.88,英文,,0,0,0,,This is a tag in HTML, and it's the HTML tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.88,1:00:26.48,英文,,0,0,0,,And a tag generally both starts and stops, or opens and closes at some point.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.48,1:00:29.78,英文,,0,0,0,,So this is the so-called start tag or open tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.78,1:00:35.54,英文,,0,0,0,,And this just means essentially to the browser, hey, browser, here comes some HTML, the language in which web pages are written.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.54,1:00:39.79,英文,,0,0,0,,This here, with the forward slash after the angled bracket,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.79,1:00:43.79,英文,,0,0,0,,Means, hey, browser, that's it for the HTML of this page. So that's what I mean by symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.79,1:00:46.33,英文,,0,0,0,,I started a thought here, finished it down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.33,1:00:48.05,英文,,0,0,0,,What's in between those two thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.05,1:00:51.65,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, here, browser, or rather, let me clarify one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.65,1:00:55.67,英文,,0,0,0,,This thing here is that other keyword, an attribute.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.67,1:00:59.36,英文,,0,0,0,,An attribute is something that modifies the behavior of a tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.36,1:01:04.20,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's similar to an argument in C or in Python, like a parameter to a function.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.20,1:01:05.80,英文,,0,0,0,,These aren't functions, but it's the same idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.80,1:01:09.07,英文,,0,0,0,,It just modifies the default behavior of something instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.07,1:01:12.67,英文,,0,0,0,,Lang equals en, you can probably guess, just means that, hey, browser.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.67,1:01:15.19,英文,,0,0,0,,Assume that everything hereafter is in English.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.19,1:01:29.28,英文,,0,0,0,,And that might be used for Google Translate or just search engine optimization so that just the server, the browser, know what human language you have actual content in, like hello, title, hello, body, even though a good computer can probably infer from context often.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.28,1:01:31.00,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so that's an attribute.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.00,1:01:32.10,英文,,0,0,0,,That's a tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.10,1:01:38.63,英文,,0,0,0,,And the whole thing here, everything in between the start tag and end tag, we would also call an HTML element.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.63,1:01:41.73,英文,,0,0,0,,That just means everything related to that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.73,1:01:43.11,英文,,0,0,0,,Open and close tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.11,1:01:55.62,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, now notice, indented inside of, so to speak, the HTML open and close tag are another pair of tags, the head tag and the body tag, or the head element collectively and the body element collectively.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.62,1:01:56.28,英文,,0,0,0,,And same idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.28,1:01:58.17,英文,,0,0,0,,Hey, browser, here comes the head of my page.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.17,1:01:59.63,英文,,0,0,0,,Hey, browser, that's it for the head.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.63,1:02:01.31,英文,,0,0,0,,Hey, browser, here comes the body of my page.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.31,1:02:03.39,英文,,0,0,0,,Hey, browser, that's it for the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.39,1:02:08.78,英文,,0,0,0,,The head is essentially the tiny little strip at the very top, including the tab itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.78,1:02:13.30,英文,,0,0,0,,The body is like 95% of everything else, the big rectangular region.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.30,1:02:16.86,英文,,0,0,0,,What's inside of your title, of your head, of the web page?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.86,1:02:18.54,英文,,0,0,0,,At the moment, just the title.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.54,1:02:21.28,英文,,0,0,0,,So this indicates, hey, browser, here comes my title.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.28,1:02:22.95,英文,,0,0,0,,Hey, browser, that's it for the title.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.95,1:02:27.09,英文,,0,0,0,,The title, of course, is literally, quote unquote, hello, comma, title.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.09,1:02:35.18,英文,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, if we bounce back out, here is the, Second element inside of the HTML tag, this says, hey, browser, here comes the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.18,1:02:36.56,英文,,0,0,0,,Hey, browser, that's it for the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.56,1:02:38.54,英文,,0,0,0,,And hey, browser, this is the contents.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.54,1:02:40.94,英文,,0,0,0,,These are the contents of the body itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.94,1:02:43.22,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, the indentation is a stylistic thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.22,1:02:48.41,英文,,0,0,0,,I did it just to be sort of neat and tidy, because it suggests what is inside of what.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.41,1:02:50.95,英文,,0,0,0,,But it also suggests a sort of hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.95,1:02:54.77,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, we'll use terminology from the world of family trees.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.77,1:03:02.48,英文,,0,0,0,,If this is like a parent, so to speak, Head and body would be the child elements of the HTML tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.48,1:03:08.72,英文,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, title is a child of the head tag, or equivalently, title is a grandchild of HTML.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.72,1:03:14.52,英文,,0,0,0,,So you can use the same sort of vernacular as in the human world when it comes to familial relationships, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.52,1:03:17.34,英文,,0,0,0,,And that just hints at, again, the same hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.34,1:03:22.24,英文,,0,0,0,,So we have tags, and they include HTML, head, title, body.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.24,1:03:23.62,英文,,0,0,0,,And that's it for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.62,1:03:24.56,英文,,0,0,0,,We have attributes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.56,1:03:27.00,英文,,0,0,0,,We've seen one example of them, lang.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.00,1:03:29.14,英文,,0,0,0,,But we'll see many other examples of the same idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.14,1:03:31.74,英文,,0,0,0,,But these building blocks are exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.74,1:03:35.83,英文,,0,0,0,,Generally, you start a thought, you finish a thought, and you might do something in between.
