Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.01,1:03:43.66,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions at all?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.66,1:03:50.22,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's now allow things to ramp up a little more interestingly and do something with these building blocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.22,1:04:00.58,英文,,0,0,0,,But so that you have a mental model for everything that's going on here on after, think of this same HTML being related in spirit to week five when we talked all about data structures.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.58,1:04:07.76,英文,,0,0,0,,If I really wanted to, I could take to heart this idea of children and parents and grandparents and really depict this thing graphically.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.76,1:04:10.18,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, this tree here, if you will,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.18,1:04:11.52,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's not a binary tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.52,1:04:12.71,英文,,0,0,0,,It's not a binary search tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.71,1:04:16.39,英文,,0,0,0,,It's just a tree using Week 5's terminology.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.39,1:04:22.49,英文,,0,0,0,,If this special node here represents the whole document, well, the root element, as I called it, is HTML.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.49,1:04:25.15,英文,,0,0,0,,HTML has two children, head and body.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.15,1:04:31.66,英文,,0,0,0,,The head tag has, in turn, a title child and, in turn, has some text, just as the body has some text.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.66,1:04:33.68,英文,,0,0,0,,And so this is what your browser is doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.68,1:04:36.46,英文,,0,0,0,,You and I, the programmers, write this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.46,1:04:40.70,英文,,0,0,0,,The browser reads this code, top to bottom, left to right, whenever you visit a website.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.70,1:04:51.70,英文,,0,0,0,,And inside of the computer's memory, Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari, whatnot, they build this data structure in the computer's memory so as to know what it is you have told them to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.70,1:05:00.61,英文,,0,0,0,,And we'll see over time, at the end of today, you can write code in an actual programming language, JavaScript, to maybe dynamically add or remove things from this tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.61,1:05:02.31,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is how things like Gmail work.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.31,1:05:05.31,英文,,0,0,0,,When you open up your Gmail inbox, if you're a Gmail user,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.31,1:05:08.53,英文,,0,0,0,,If you just stay there long enough, you'll probably get more and more mail.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.53,1:05:13.07,英文,,0,0,0,,And what happens? You don't have to reload the page or rebuild the tree, per se.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.07,1:05:16.72,英文,,0,0,0,,It just all of a sudden appears at the top, at the top, at the top.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.72,1:05:25.06,英文,,0,0,0,,What's happening there is that Google wrote some code that just keeps adding more nodes to this tree every time they realize you've got a new message again and again.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.06,1:05:33.45,英文,,0,0,0,,So that's the relationship now, even with this world of HTML, with all of the programmatic ideas we looked at. In the past.
