Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.92,1:07:57.12,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to click Back to go back to that index of all of my files, which I started at earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.12,1:08:02.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And you'll see now that I have two files, because I obviously just created a second file called paragraphs.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.15,1:08:05.73,英文,,0,0,0,,So let's click on this to see our three paragraphs of Latin-like text.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.73,1:08:09.34,英文,,0,0,0,,And voila, I'll zoom out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.34,1:08:11.36,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, first bug, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.36,1:08:16.93,英文,,0,0,0,,This just looks like one massive blob of text, not three blobs of text.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.93,1:08:17.95,英文,,0,0,0,,And why might that be?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.95,1:08:22.46,英文,,0,0,0,,Borrowing the hint I offered a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.46,1:08:24.71,英文,,0,0,0,,Why are we not seeing break?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.71,1:08:29.43,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so we need some kind of line breaks here, because the browser, turns out, is only going to take us literally.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.43,1:08:32.63,英文,,0,0,0,,And if you just give it text, text, text, it's just going to show you text.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.63,1:08:40.75,英文,,0,0,0,,And any time there's more than a single white space, whether it's 2, or 20, or 200, it's going to just assume that you did that just to be neat and tidy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.75,1:08:44.67,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's going to collapse them into just one space visually, like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.67,1:08:47.29,英文,,0,0,0,,So there are, in fact, a couple of solutions.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.29,1:08:48.49,英文,,0,0,0,,One is this here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.49,1:08:50.27,英文,,0,0,0,,I could add some explicit line breaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.27,1:08:53.87,英文,,0,0,0,,And it turns out. that there's a br tag like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.87,1:08:56.35,英文,,0,0,0,,And just for visibility's sake, let me do two of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.35,1:08:59.02,英文,,0,0,0,,So like hitting Enter, Enter on my keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.02,1:09:01.76,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll do it here too, br for break, break.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.76,1:09:03.84,英文,,0,0,0,,And now let me go back to my other tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.84,1:09:06.58,英文,,0,0,0,,Nothing's changed yet, but that's because I have to reload.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.58,1:09:10.74,英文,,0,0,0,,I've changed it on the server, but now I need to change it in the browser by reloading.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.74,1:09:13.80,英文,,0,0,0,,And now it looks a little better, albeit nonsensical.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.80,1:09:15.97,英文,,0,0,0,,But you'll notice a curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.97,1:09:18.91,英文,,0,0,0,,Per this br tag, this is kind of poorly designed.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.91,1:09:22.93,英文,,0,0,0,,It's a little hackish to just say, enter, enter, and make the browser do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.93,1:09:28.04,英文,,0,0,0,,Breaks, line breaks, don't actually require close tags or end tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.04,1:09:33.12,英文,,0,0,0,,So not all tags need to be closed, at least those that it just makes no semantic sense to close them, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.12,1:09:35.31,英文,,0,0,0,,Like the break is there or it's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.31,1:09:40.11,英文,,0,0,0,,You can't imagine starting to move to the next line and then eventually getting around to finishing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.11,1:09:41.71,英文,,0,0,0,,It's either there or it's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.71,1:09:45.32,英文,,0,0,0,,So some tags do not have closed tags, as necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.32,1:09:50.56,英文,,0,0,0,,But there's a more elegant way here, I dare say, not just sort of hackishly putting in these line breaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.56,1:09:51.70,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me do this instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.70,1:09:53.24,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll delete those.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.24,1:09:58.46,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me go ahead and, as the name of this file suggests, let me add a paragraph tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.46,1:10:03.57,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, here I need to fight with VS Code's autocomplete, because I don't want to finish the thought there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.57,1:10:07.27,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and open the paragraph tag and close a paragraph tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.27,1:10:12.67,英文,,0,0,0,,And just to keep things tidy, I'll go ahead and indent to, even though the indentation itself doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.67,1:10:16.51,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and create another tag for opening this paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.51,1:10:18.89,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'll close this one here.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.89,1:10:20.01,英文,,0,0,0,,And now let me see.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.01,1:10:21.85,英文,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's fighting with my autocomplete.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.85,1:10:25.30,英文,,0,0,0,,But that's fine, because I did this sort of the wrong way at first.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.30,1:10:31.02,英文,,0,0,0,,And now let me go ahead and finish this thought by closing this paragraph tag here.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.02,1:10:33.66,英文,,0,0,0,,And I've manually fixed all of my indentations.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.66,1:10:38.24,英文,,0,0,0,,So now on line 10, I have the equivalent of, hey, browser, start a paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.24,1:10:40.07,英文,,0,0,0,,And then it does the Latin-like text.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.07,1:10:42.99,英文,,0,0,0,,Then on line 12, hey, browser, that's it for this paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.99,1:10:44.77,英文,,0,0,0,,And repeat, repeat.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.77,1:10:48.13,英文,,0,0,0,,If I now go back to my other tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.13,1:10:51.17,英文,,0,0,0,,And reload again shouldn't be all that different.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.17,1:10:53.54,英文,,0,0,0,,But semantically, it's a little bit better.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.54,1:10:54.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.08,1:10:56.88,英文,,0,0,0,,Because just saying break break doesn't really mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.88,1:11:02.18,英文,,0,0,0,,But by saying paragraph, paragraph, paragraph, now there's some more semantic information there.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.18,1:11:09.13,英文,,0,0,0,,Now if Google is analyzing your page, or if the programmer is trying to understand what it is you did in the past when writing this code,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.13,1:11:14.60,英文,,0,0,0,,You just know semantically, oh, this is a paragraph, this is a paragraph, this is a paragraph, just like in a book or an essay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.60,1:11:20.25,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's a little more clear, focusing more on what it is, not how you want to display it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.25,1:11:25.30,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions, then, on these paragraphs?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.30,1:11:26.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, all right, so a few more tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.84,1:11:33.54,英文,,0,0,0,,And indeed, these first few examples will really just be like sort of bang, bang, bang, just a bunch of different vocabulary words in the form of these new tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.54,1:11:35.96,英文,,0,0,0,,But we won't go through the entire laundry list of tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.96,1:11:41.87,英文,,0,0,0,,This is indeed the thing for which web references and books and the like are ultimately helpful, just like a dictionary in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.87,1:11:42.97,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to go ahead and do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.97,1:11:44.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and copy this.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.73,1:11:49.69,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me create a new file called headings.html, just so we have a new file for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.69,1:11:53.37,英文,,0,0,0,,To save time, I'm just going to paste that exact same code just to get me started.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.37,1:11:57.21,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to change the title of it for clarity for the code online to Headings.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.21,1:12:02.92,英文,,0,0,0,,And now, just like a book or an essay or a thesis, let me actually put some actual headings here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.92,1:12:07.40,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, if my first heading, like Chapter 1, I could do something like this up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.40,1:12:09.66,英文,,0,0,0,,I could have a paragraph, like I just learned.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.66,1:12:12.46,英文,,0,0,0,,And I could say something like Chapter 1 here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.46,1:12:14.02,英文,,0,0,0,,But that's not really a paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.02,1:12:18.81,英文,,0,0,0,,And so it's sort of better designed to tell the browser and really tell the world what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.81,1:12:24.23,英文,,0,0,0,,So it turns out there's another tag I can use, like h1, for heading and most important heading.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.23,1:12:26.89,英文,,0,0,0,,And in here, I'm just going to keep it simple, and I'm going to say something like 1.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.89,1:12:31.76,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, this is so short, here's a good candidate for just keeping this all on the same line.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.76,1:12:36.70,英文,,0,0,0,,But this has no functional difference, but it'll just make it a little more terse on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.70,1:12:38.92,英文,,0,0,0,,Now let me go ahead down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.92,1:12:41.91,英文,,0,0,0,,And I could have multiple headings, so H1, 2.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.91,1:12:45.41,英文,,0,0,0,,And down here, I could have another one, H1, 3.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.41,1:12:48.46,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I go back to my other tab, I reload it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.46,1:12:54.04,英文,,0,0,0,,Now we should see, just like a book or an essay, now we have some proper.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.04,1:12:56.76,英文,,0,0,0,,Now we have some, oops, I have to go to the right file, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.76,1:13:01.74,英文,,0,0,0,,If I go back to the index, now we see the new third file called headings.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.74,1:13:05.99,英文,,0,0,0,,And now we indeed see some fairly pretty, if simple, headings as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.99,1:13:15.31,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, if these aren't three chapters, 1, 2, 3, but maybe it's a chapter, then a section, then a subsection, such that just visually you want things to get smaller and smaller, well, those exist too.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.31,1:13:17.87,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, you can do h1 through h6.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.87,1:13:20.85,英文,,0,0,0,,h1, a little paradoxically, is the biggest and boldest.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.85,1:13:23.20,英文,,0,0,0,,h6 is the smallest, but still bold.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.20,1:13:33.62,英文,,0,0,0,,So it might make sense to make this h2 both open and close, and maybe this h3 open and close if, again, this is a section or a subsection inside of that chapter.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.62,1:13:36.64,英文,,0,0,0,,If I reload now, notice it just gets a little smaller.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.64,1:13:39.93,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's more similar to what you'd see on the printed page.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.93,1:13:44.55,英文,,0,0,0,,But this now is just another three tags that I might use in my own code.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.55,1:13:46.73,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, well, how about lists of things?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.73,1:13:48.93,英文,,0,0,0,,I have three paragraphs here, but let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.93,1:13:50.81,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go back to VS Code.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.81,1:13:53.29,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to copy this code so I have a starting point.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.29,1:13:57.98,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to create a new file called, say, list.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.98,1:13:59.24,英文,,0,0,0,,Here, I'm going to copy-paste.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.24,1:14:02.40,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to change my title to be List, just for clarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.40,1:14:08.54,英文,,0,0,0,,And in here, I'm going to go ahead and get rid of this whole body, because let's move away from these massive paragraphs and keep it simpler for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.54,1:14:16.94,英文,,0,0,0,,If I want to have a list of things, for instance, if you haven't seen these already, a computer scientist, when they're fishing for just some arbitrary, meaningless words,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.94,1:14:20.16,英文,,0,0,0,,They often use foo, bar, and baz, just as their go-to.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.16,1:14:23.17,英文,,0,0,0,,Just like a mathematician might use x, y, z for variables.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.17,1:14:25.67,英文,,0,0,0,,So foo, bar, and baz are on three separate lines.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.67,1:14:28.39,英文,,0,0,0,,And maybe this is like my to-do list or my shopping list.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.39,1:14:36.20,英文,,0,0,0,,But you can probably imagine if I go back to my other tab, go back to the index, I now see my new file, list.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.20,1:14:38.54,英文,,0,0,0,,But it's probably going to look wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.54,1:14:44.12,英文,,0,0,0,,I think I'm just going to say, yeah, foo bar baz, all in one breath, if you will, not on new lines.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.12,1:14:45.46,英文,,0,0,0,,And you can try to fight this.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.46,1:14:50.43,英文,,0,0,0,,You can be like, I really want to put some line breaks there, go back and reload.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.43,1:14:52.41,英文,,0,0,0,,It's still not going to make any change.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.41,1:14:55.33,英文,,0,0,0,,How do I want to fix this? Well, I can do this in a few ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.33,1:14:58.53,英文,,0,0,0,,I could make them paragraphs. But they're not really paragraphs. They're a list.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.53,1:15:01.06,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to use a different tag instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.06,1:15:07.06,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to create, for instance, an unordered list using the ul tag, open and close.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.06,1:15:11.76,英文,,0,0,0,,Inside of that, I'm going to use the list item tag, li, and I'm going to say foo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.76,1:15:13.83,英文,,0,0,0,,Inside of another tag, I'm going to say bar.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.83,1:15:17.31,英文,,0,0,0,,Inside of a third tag, open and close, I'm going to say baz.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.31,1:15:20.51,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's getting a little verbose, but it's still relatively succinct.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.51,1:15:23.43,英文,,0,0,0,,Li is all you need type for list item.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.43,1:15:26.17,英文,,0,0,0,,Ul is all you need type for unordered list.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.17,1:15:29.13,英文,,0,0,0,,So there's some shorthand syntax here that's adopted.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.13,1:15:39.69,英文,,0,0,0,,If I now reload, you're going to see a so-called unordered list, like not sorted, which means by convention to show it as bullets, though it could be displayed in different ways visually as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.69,1:15:49.24,英文,,0,0,0,,If you actually change your mind and you realize, oh, I'd really like to number this, well, you could obviously just add one, And 2 and 3. But that's going to get annoying, especially if the list grows.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.24,1:15:52.69,英文,,0,0,0,,You want to change something, insert something in the middle, then you have to reorder it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.69,1:15:54.93,英文,,0,0,0,,I mean, we're using computers here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.93,1:15:56.39,英文,,0,0,0,,They can do this for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.39,1:16:00.34,英文,,0,0,0,,So we can change the ul, too. Any guesses?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.34,1:16:03.95,英文,,0,0,0,,OL, maybe, for ordered list, which is sort of the opposite here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.95,1:16:06.17,英文,,0,0,0,,So let's try changing that to OL.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.17,1:16:07.69,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go back to my browser.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.69,1:16:12.79,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm just hitting Command-R or Control-R to reload the page instead of clicking the button every time.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.79,1:16:16.24,英文,,0,0,0,,Now I automatically get 1, 2, and 3.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.24,1:16:20.48,英文,,0,0,0,,And you can even override the aesthetics using different numerables or symbology instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.48,1:16:24.43,英文,,0,0,0,,But that would be perhaps the most common there as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.43,1:16:31.77,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, it's a lot of tags quickly, but any questions on lists, paragraphs, headings, or the like?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.77,1:16:35.41,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so let me go ahead and propose this here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.41,1:16:38.64,英文,,0,0,0,,Let's go ahead and create what we'll call a table.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.64,1:16:44.00,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me copy and paste this into a new file, code of table.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.00,1:16:47.44,英文,,0,0,0,,And in table.html, let me again rename the title to table.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.44,1:16:50.41,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me get rid of that ordered list from before.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.41,1:16:53.63,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me now use a table tag, open and close.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.63,1:17:00.03,英文,,0,0,0,,This one's a little weird, but inside of a table, you typically have a head of the table.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.03,1:17:02.25,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll say, well, let's say the first row.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.25,1:17:03.56,英文,,0,0,0,,We'll keep this one simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.56,1:17:05.86,英文,,0,0,0,,A table row, or TR.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.86,1:17:09.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Inside of a table row, you would ideally have columns.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.08,1:17:10.40,英文,,0,0,0,,But that's not the nomenclature.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.40,1:17:11.44,英文,,0,0,0,,Instead, you have data.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.44,1:17:13.30,英文,,0,0,0,,So TD for table data.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.30,1:17:16.08,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me go ahead and just have the first datum be 1.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.08,1:17:19.67,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to arbitrarily do 1, 2, 3, just so we have something to play with.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.67,1:17:24.77,英文,,0,0,0,,And you know what? Just for demonstration's sake, I am going to deliberately copy paste this twice.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.77,1:17:31.21,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm just going to manually change the numbers, just so we can see what I'm creating. 789.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.21,1:17:43.30,英文,,0,0,0,,And then maybe just for good measure, if you're seeing where this is going, let me copy this one more time and give myself a final row with an asterisk, a 0, and a pound sign, if maybe you see where this is going.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.30,1:17:45.06,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go back to my other tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.06,1:17:47.28,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go back to the index.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.28,1:17:49.49,英文,,0,0,0,,There's my new file, table.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.49,1:17:50.61,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll click that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.61,1:17:53.61,英文,,0,0,0,,And while it's not very pretty, I'll zoom in.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.61,1:17:55.75,英文,,0,0,0,,It's indeed a table of data.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.75,1:17:59.07,英文,,0,0,0,,I happen to mimic a telephone keypad.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.07,1:18:08.66,英文,,0,0,0,,But you could imagine this being much juicier, much more interesting scientific or financial data or the like laid out into these rows, TRs, and these columns, a.k.a. table data as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.66,1:18:11.72,英文,,0,0,0,,So we have that ability as well for structured data.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.72,1:18:14.92,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, the internet has lots of images on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.92,1:18:16.84,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, this is all just text.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.84,1:18:18.50,英文,,0,0,0,,How can we introduce images?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.50,1:18:21.01,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, let me go ahead and do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.01,1:18:30.01,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me first. Sort of semi-secretly copy an image file that I brought from earlier just so we have something to play with.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.01,1:18:34.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And I have in my account here now an image called harvard.jpeg.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.15,1:18:39.73,英文,,0,0,0,,And I uploaded this semi-secretly a second ago into my account so that I can reference a second file.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.73,1:18:43.95,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and copy this HTML just to save myself some keystrokes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.95,1:18:47.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and do code of image.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.73,1:18:50.53,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me paste that code and hide my terminal window.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.53,1:18:54.47,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get rid of all of this table as just uninteresting now.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.47,1:19:01.61,英文,,0,0,0,,We're going to make this even simpler by changing my title to Image to keep all these demonstrations separate.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.61,1:19:10.80,英文,,0,0,0,,And now, if I want to make a web page that, when visited, shows us a picture of Harvard, well, there's an image tag, abbreviated IMG for short.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.80,1:19:13.36,英文,,0,0,0,,I can specify what the source of that image is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.36,1:19:21.06,英文,,0,0,0,,And if my file, a JPEG in this case, is literally in the same folder, I can just say, quote unquote, harvard.jpeg.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.06,1:19:25.07,英文,,0,0,0,,If it's in a folder, I should mention the folder name in a slash or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.07,1:19:35.02,英文,,0,0,0,,If the image is on the internet somewhere with a URL, I could also have a whole URL, HTTPS colon slash slash, and then the URL of the image. But I upload it in advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.02,1:19:37.14,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, this is just going to visually display on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.14,1:19:39.34,英文,,0,0,0,,But not everyone, of course, can see images.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.34,1:19:41.49,英文,,0,0,0,,Screen readers might need a bit of assistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.49,1:19:46.37,英文,,0,0,0,,And even search engines might want to analyze the page and know what this is an image of.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.37,1:19:51.22,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, machine learning and artificial intelligence are maybe getting better, to be fair, at figuring out.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.22,1:19:54.34,英文,,0,0,0,,just by analyzing images what they are. But they're certainly imperfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.34,1:19:58.00,英文,,0,0,0,,I am a human. I know pretty well what I took a photo of, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.00,1:20:13.25,英文,,0,0,0,,So maybe what I should do proactively, which would be good for accessibility, is have this alt tag for alternative text, and then literally say, like, Harvard University, so that someone who can't see or so that a server can actually know with higher probability what it is they're looking at.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.25,1:20:18.25,英文,,0,0,0,,And I could be even more detailed than just a phrase. I could describe the image as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.25,1:20:22.03,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, let me go back to my index in the second tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.03,1:20:24.89,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go back and zoom back out.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.89,1:20:29.54,英文,,0,0,0,,There's my new file, and there's my new JPEG that I quickly uploaded before.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.54,1:20:37.07,英文,,0,0,0,,I can click now on image.html, and albeit a little overwhelming, that is a really big image of Harvard.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.07,1:20:40.35,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, apparently, it's too big to fit on the screen, so this isn't the best
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.35,1:20:42.45,英文,,0,0,0,,user experience to have to scroll up.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.45,1:20:44.05,英文,,0,0,0,,OK, so there's the image.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.05,1:20:47.96,英文,,0,0,0,,Horrible, horrible design, if you will, at least in terms of my code.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.96,1:20:52.78,英文,,0,0,0,,But there's going to be ways where I can sort of rein that in and affect the height or the width as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.78,1:20:57.29,英文,,0,0,0,,But for now, it's just deliberately a little overwhelming instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.29,1:21:00.91,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, we can do something a little more fun and topical today.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.91,1:21:03.61,英文,,0,0,0,,Which might be to use a video instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.61,1:21:15.42,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me go ahead here and very quickly grab another file today, which I brought in advance and that you might have seen briefly earlier, which is an MP4, an actual video file.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.42,1:21:21.22,英文,,0,0,0,,And what I'm going to do here, by revealing VS Code again, is I'm going to code a file called video.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.22,1:21:23.18,英文,,0,0,0,,Yet another demonstration here.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.18,1:21:26.95,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to change my title to video, just to keep these things straight.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.95,1:21:31.53,英文,,0,0,0,,And instead of the image tag, you might imagine using now, indeed, a video tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.53,1:21:37.33,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is a relatively newer tag that has increasing support among browsers, so it's good now to use.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.33,1:21:40.35,英文,,0,0,0,,And inside of this, the syntax is a little different.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.35,1:21:45.77,英文,,0,0,0,,You specify, and this is weirdly, annoyingly inconsistent, not SRC for source.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.77,1:21:47.62,英文,,0,0,0,,You literally say source.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.62,1:21:50.60,英文,,0,0,0,,And then in source, you use a source attribute.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.60,1:21:54.40,英文,,0,0,0,,Horrible design, semantically. But this is what we're stuck with.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.40,1:22:00.86,英文,,0,0,0,,Halloween.mp4 is the name of the video we upload in advance, made by some of Harvard's digital artists.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.86,1:22:05.57,英文,,0,0,0,,And the type of this video, so that the browser knows for sure, is video slash mp4.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.57,1:22:09.67,英文,,0,0,0,,That's a so-called content type that you just know or you look up to figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.67,1:22:17.43,英文,,0,0,0,,And just so that this is as animated as possible, I'm going to tell the video tag with a few attributes to autoplay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.43,1:22:29.04,英文,,0,0,0,,And it turns out that attributes often have key value pairs, whereby it's the key, the attribute name, equals quote, unquote, some value, just like lang equals quote, unquote, en for English.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.04,1:22:30.90,英文,,0,0,0,,But not all attributes need values.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.90,1:22:38.34,英文,,0,0,0,,In fact, if you read the documentation for HTML's video tag, there's an autoplay attribute where you can literally just say the key, and it needs no value.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.34,1:22:39.68,英文,,0,0,0,,It's just going to mean autoplay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.68,1:22:42.99,英文,,0,0,0,,And if you don't want to autoplay, you just omit it altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.99,1:22:45.95,英文,,0,0,0,,So you don't necessarily need a value on or off.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.95,1:22:48.05,英文,,0,0,0,,I want the thing to loop just so it keeps going.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.05,1:22:50.73,英文,,0,0,0,,I want it to be muted so that we don't hear any sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.73,1:22:51.95,英文,,0,0,0,,In fact, there is no sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.95,1:23:03.33,英文,,0,0,0,,But browsers nowadays, for anti-spam and advertising reasons, often will not play a video if it has sound because it's just kind of obnoxious if you visit a page and all of a sudden your speakers start blaring.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.33,1:23:08.35,英文,,0,0,0,,So I know this from having read up on this that I should mute it if I wanted to actually autoplay for real.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.35,1:23:10.83,英文,,0,0,0,,And then I'll set the width manually for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.83,1:23:14.86,英文,,0,0,0,,to be like 128 pixels across, just from some trial and error earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.86,1:23:18.90,英文,,0,0,0,,And that with attribute does have a value.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.90,1:23:24.12,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm being a little uptight here by alphabetizing all of my attributes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.12,1:23:25.20,英文,,0,0,0,,Not at all necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.20,1:23:28.29,英文,,0,0,0,,I do it just so I can skim things faster and know if something is there or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.29,1:23:30.51,英文,,0,0,0,,So for me, it's just a matter of style.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.51,1:23:39.43,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go back to my other tab, go back to my index, and you'll see two new files again, the mp4 file and video.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.43,1:23:40.57,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll click on the latter.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.57,1:23:49.09,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I did this well, here we have, thanks to our friends in Harvard, our artistic friends at Harvard, very
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.09,1:23:54.85,英文,,0,0,0,,Like an ooh would help with the drama here. But OK. But we have a very dramatic, nice Halloween-type view here as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.85,1:23:56.69,英文,,0,0,0,,So we have videos embedded as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.69,1:24:03.96,英文,,0,0,0,,And suffice it to say, there's ways to embed YouTube videos or Vimeo or other services as well using yet more tags too.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.96,1:24:10.38,英文,,0,0,0,,But the web is, of course, all about Hyperlink, hypertext markup language, where you click on something and you end up somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.38,1:24:13.53,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is how the web is so powerfully interconnected.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.53,1:24:20.21,英文,,0,0,0,,So how do we start creating links from one website or web page to another, either that I made or someone else?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.21,1:24:23.62,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, let me go ahead and open back up my terminal window.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.62,1:24:28.74,英文,,0,0,0,,And let's create a file called link.html, just to demonstrate what you and I know as a link.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.74,1:24:30.16,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll hide my terminal window now.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.16,1:24:32.96,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me copy-paste just to save myself some keystrokes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.96,1:24:36.60,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me get rid of the video tag so we can focus now on links.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.60,1:24:40.19,英文,,0,0,0,,Suppose that I want you to visit Harvard virtually.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.19,1:24:44.49,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, I could say something like, visit Harvard, period.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.49,1:24:46.83,英文,,0,0,0,,This is uninteresting because it's just going to be text.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.83,1:24:51.43,英文,,0,0,0,,I probably want you to actually visit harvard.edu instead, more specifically.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.43,1:24:55.51,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'll lowercase it just to be consistent with what browsers do in the address bar.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.51,1:25:01.45,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, let me go now back to this Video tab and go back where we now see my index.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.45,1:25:04.14,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll zoom back in, and there's link.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.14,1:25:08.44,英文,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, when I click this and I'll zoom in, you literally just see the text that I wrote.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.44,1:25:18.34,英文,,0,0,0,,And yet, on every social media platform nowadays, except like Instagram, when you type a URL or what looks like a URL, even if you didn't bother with the HTTP or HTTPS,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.34,1:25:23.12,英文,,0,0,0,,It usually automatically links it for you on Facebook, on Twitter, and other sites as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.12,1:25:24.93,英文,,0,0,0,,That's just a convenience.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.93,1:25:26.85,英文,,0,0,0,,Discord and Slack do that too.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.85,1:25:29.63,英文,,0,0,0,,But they're just doing it to make things more user-friendly.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.63,1:25:35.69,英文,,0,0,0,,But they have to generate HTML with the proper tags and attributes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.69,1:25:42.07,英文,,0,0,0,,So to get this to actually work, it's not even good enough to say HTTPS colon slash slash www.harvard.edu.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.07,1:25:46.63,英文,,0,0,0,,Because if I go back now and reload now, you'll literally just see all of that as text.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.63,1:25:51.83,英文,,0,0,0,,If you want the browser to treat this as a link, you need to use the anchor tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.83,1:25:57.02,英文,,0,0,0,,It'd be great if it were called the link tag, but it's not. It's called the anchor tag, or A for short.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.02,1:26:03.94,英文,,0,0,0,,And the way you reference the URL to which you want to lead the user is via href, for hyper-reference.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.94,1:26:07.00,英文,,0,0,0,,One of the earliest tags, perhaps among the most arcane now.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.00,1:26:18.31,英文,,0,0,0,,But if I then put that whole URL in quotes and close my tag, I now have an opportunity to finish my thought in between the start tag and the end tag for this anchor.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.31,1:26:23.02,英文,,0,0,0,,And what I put in between the start and end tag is whatever the human's going to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.02,1:26:25.28,英文,,0,0,0,,So here I can say Harvard.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.28,1:26:27.12,英文,,0,0,0,,I can go back to my other tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.12,1:26:28.80,英文,,0,0,0,,I can reload the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.80,1:26:31.76,英文,,0,0,0,,And now you see the familiar blue underline.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.76,1:26:33.63,英文,,0,0,0,,This now is an actual link.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.63,1:26:38.39,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I click it, I'll be whisked away to the actual Harvard website.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.39,1:26:40.45,英文,,0,0,0,,But there's a risk here.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.45,1:26:50.95,英文,,0,0,0,,Can anyone imagine, pretty simply, after, like, what, 60 seconds of the anchor tag, how could someone, an adversary, misuse this tag alone?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.95,1:26:57.29,英文,,0,0,0,,How could a website run by an adversary, how could a spammer misuse this tag, do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.29,1:27:01.47,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.47,1:27:02.49,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.49,1:27:05.91,英文,,0,0,0,,You could have it say one thing but lead elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.91,1:27:07.89,英文,,0,0,0,,So I could say, Yale in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.89,1:27:09.77,英文,,0,0,0,,Nothing's stopping me as the developer.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.77,1:27:11.11,英文,,0,0,0,,Go back to the page, reload.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.11,1:27:12.57,英文,,0,0,0,,Now it says, visit Yale.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.57,1:27:16.15,英文,,0,0,0,,You click on Yale, and voila, you end up applying to the wrong place instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.15,1:27:18.20,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, there's some hints of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.20,1:27:20.88,英文,,0,0,0,,I could hover over this, and super small.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.88,1:27:24.10,英文,,0,0,0,,This isn't very good for your anti-hacking techniques.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.10,1:27:28.08,英文,,0,0,0,,But way down here, you can actually see the URL that it's going to go to.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.08,1:27:31.27,英文,,0,0,0,,And most browsers, indeed, do this, at least on desktops and laptops.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.27,1:27:32.67,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's a little bit of a hint.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.67,1:27:42.60,英文,,0,0,0,,But what you're seeing here, even though this is kind of a silly, playful example, this is exactly how phishing attacks work, P-H-I-S-H-I-N-G work,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.60,1:27:48.04,英文,,0,0,0,,Whereby an adversary tells you to log into your PayPal account, but it doesn't go to paypal.com.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.04,1:27:54.88,英文,,0,0,0,,It goes to some other random website that they bought and built that then tries to collect your username and password and store it in their database.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.88,1:27:58.13,英文,,0,0,0,,So now they can log into your PayPal account as you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.13,1:28:01.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And it boils down to that simple primitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.15,1:28:03.63,英文,,0,0,0,,And you can be even more manipulative, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.63,1:28:12.80,英文,,0,0,0,,You can even say the whole URL for Yale, like yale.edu, or worse, https://www.yale.edu, reload that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.80,1:28:20.74,英文,,0,0,0,,And now, I mean, who among you and people in your lives are necessarily going to be so paranoid as to not just blindly click on that URL?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.74,1:28:26.51,英文,,0,0,0,,This is why just being a defensive, real-world person nowadays digitally is just ever more so important.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.51,1:28:32.97,英文,,0,0,0,,So these same things that can be used for good or benign use cases can also be used for ill purposes, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.97,1:28:35.69,英文,,0,0,0,,And it is literally that simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.69,1:28:40.30,英文,,0,0,0,,Questions now on any of these tags thus far?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.30,1:28:42.98,英文,,0,0,0,,Just a few more to offer up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.98,1:28:46.29,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions on this here?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.29,1:28:46.55,英文,,0,0,0,,No?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.55,1:28:52.61,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, let me open up a couple that I brought in advance just so we don't have to type all of them here.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.61,1:29:08.07,英文,,0,0,0,,If you, for instance, have a web page that's got quite a bit of code, let me go ahead and grab from the website a couple of examples real fast here, namely one that we'll call, how about, meta.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.07,1:29:15.13,英文,,0,0,0,,And in this example here, give me just a moment to full screen it, we're going to have a file.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.13,1:29:17.46,英文,,0,0,0,,So code meta.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.46,1:29:19.00,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll open this up next.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.00,1:29:21.62,英文,,0,0,0,,No relationship to what we now know as meta the company.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.62,1:29:27.22,英文,,0,0,0,,But rather, this is going to be a page that I copied and pasted the same chunk of Latin-like text from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.22,1:29:29.55,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's going to be a really big paragraph of text.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.55,1:29:34.37,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is an example where if you were to open this web page, not on my own Mac or your PC, but on your phone,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.37,1:29:37.63,英文,,0,0,0,,The font might actually be really annoying and difficult to read. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.63,1:29:44.16,英文,,0,0,0,,Because your phone's going to try to squeeze all of the content onto the tiny viewport, the rectangular region of your phone instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.16,1:29:51.86,英文,,0,0,0,,So it turns out there are ways, pretty easy ways, to make your website mobile-friendly as well, otherwise known technically as responsive.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.86,1:29:57.16,英文,,0,0,0,,And the easiest way to do this is to include this tag here.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.16,1:29:59.74,英文,,0,0,0,,A meta tag, again, no relationship to Facebook.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.74,1:30:01.24,英文,,0,0,0,,This has been here much longer.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.24,1:30:07.21,英文,,0,0,0,,And this case here, this meta tag on line 5, has its own sort of approach to key value pairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.21,1:30:10.51,英文,,0,0,0,,This is a good example of where it'd be nice if it looked just like everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.51,1:30:13.05,英文,,0,0,0,,But this is what we have historically.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.05,1:30:18.41,英文,,0,0,0,,You can have a meta tag with an attribute called name that refers to the name of some feature of the browser.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.41,1:30:25.46,英文,,0,0,0,,In this case, viewport is the technical term for the big rectangular region to which I keep referring, the body, really, of your page.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.46,1:30:30.30,英文,,0,0,0,,The content for the viewport, you can say some esoteric details like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.30,1:30:32.04,英文,,0,0,0,,The initial scale should be 1.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.04,1:30:35.37,英文,,0,0,0,,That is, no matter who visits your site, it shouldn't start zoomed in.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.37,1:30:36.65,英文,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't start zoomed out.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.65,1:30:39.07,英文,,0,0,0,,It should start at just the default sizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.07,1:30:47.98,英文,,0,0,0,,And then this here, width equals device width, is a very arcane way of saying, if the user has a small screen, Show the text proportional to that size.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.98,1:30:50.90,英文,,0,0,0,,Don't just try to cram it all into a tiny little window.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.90,1:30:52.26,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's super simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.26,1:31:01.60,英文,,0,0,0,,But if, for the next problem set or future projects as well, you find that just things look really bad on mobile, this kind of tag is the place to start meta.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.60,1:31:06.74,英文,,0,0,0,,There aren't terribly many of these that you'll use, but they're useful for other mechanisms as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.74,1:31:11.43,英文,,0,0,0,,In fact, let me go ahead and semi-secretly pull up one other example as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.43,1:31:16.71,英文,,0,0,0,,whereby I'm going to grab another example that uses more of these tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.71,1:31:20.28,英文,,0,0,0,,And in just a moment, I'll reveal it here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.28,1:31:23.04,英文,,0,0,0,,Give me just one second here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.04,1:31:29.42,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll propose that in this example of meta,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.42,1:31:33.40,英文,,0,0,0,,We now add these properties instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.40,1:31:37.82,英文,,0,0,0,,So I copy pasted this from an existing file, just so as to not waste time typing all of these out.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.82,1:31:48.54,英文,,0,0,0,,If you've ever shared a URL on Facebook, or Twitter, or Slack, or Discord, or any number of websites nowadays that automatically show a nice preview, where you suddenly see the default image of the page, maybe
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.54,1:31:52.32,英文,,0,0,0,,Maybe a few sentences or words of text or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.32,1:31:59.90,英文,,0,0,0,,Sometimes those applications, those websites, will just choose the first image it finds on the website or the first sentence it sees and show that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.90,1:32:03.62,英文,,0,0,0,,But that might not be very user-friendly or search engine friendly.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.62,1:32:11.51,英文,,0,0,0,,And so a developer might want to control what it is that Slack, Discord, Facebook, Twitter, and other such sites show by default.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.51,1:32:18.25,英文,,0,0,0,,For that, you can use nowadays what are called open graph tags, which is to say there's other uses of the meta tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.25,1:32:19.43,英文,,0,0,0,,And you just look these things up.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.43,1:32:22.30,英文,,0,0,0,,Even I had to look this up to remember what the key value pairs are.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.30,1:32:34.45,英文,,0,0,0,,The meta tag can also have a property attribute that can be these very specific strings, ogTitle, ogDescription, ogImage, which denotes open graph, which, again, is this standard that's evolved in recent years.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.45,1:32:49.69,英文,,0,0,0,,And what you can do here is tell browsers, and in turn servers, what you want them to show as the default title of the page, the description of the page, and even the default image, just so you can exercise more control when sharing things socially nowadays as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.69,1:32:51.86,英文,,0,0,0,,Again, it just boils down to these key value pairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.86,1:32:55.14,英文,,0,0,0,,This is absolutely the kind of thing you look up as needed to cross-check.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.14,1:32:56.46,英文,,0,0,0,,But those capabilities are there.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.46,1:33:12.66,英文,,0,0,0,,And so literally, the next time you paste a link into Slack or Discord or any online site that then displays it in embedded fashion, just know that all this time, a little bit of textual code like this in HTML has been there by whoever authored the site.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.66,1:33:21.85,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, let's do one final example in HTML alone before we transition to just cleaning up the aesthetics and improving the visuals of everything we've been creating.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.85,1:33:24.85,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead here and close meta.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.85,1:33:38.24,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me code up a new file called howaboutsearch.html and see if we can't draw some inspiration from our cursory understanding earlier of how URLs work to see if we can't reinvent google.com itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.24,1:33:41.46,英文,,0,0,0,,So recall that a canonical URL might look like this here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.46,1:33:50.67,英文,,0,0,0,,And in particular, if you want to pass in user input to that URL, again, you can potentially have a question mark and then a key equals value pair.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.67,1:33:55.82,英文,,0,0,0,,Or for that matter, you can even have multiple key value pairs that, by convention, are separated by ampersand.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.82,1:33:56.80,英文,,0,0,0,,These things are everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.80,1:34:04.44,英文,,0,0,0,,Like later today, when you pull up almost any website in your browser, look at the URL, and you'll just see a lot of this, a lot of noise, too, and distractions.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.44,1:34:08.55,英文,,0,0,0,,But there's going to be some equal signs, most likely, and or some ampersands as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.55,1:34:11.33,英文,,0,0,0,,And those are just separating key value pairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.33,1:34:12.55,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, what can I do here?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.55,1:34:18.10,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, if you think back to how we manually searched for cats earlier, Let me quickly do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.10,1:34:19.44,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll do this one manually.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.44,1:34:22.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Doc type HTML as my very first line.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.84,1:34:29.85,英文,,0,0,0,,HTML tag with, how about my lang attribute for English up here. And then inside of this, I'll have a head tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.85,1:34:34.61,英文,,0,0,0,,Inside of this, I'll have a title. I'll call this example Search.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.61,1:34:37.33,英文,,0,0,0,,And then down here, I'll have my beginning of a body tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.33,1:34:48.42,英文,,0,0,0,,And now, let me introduce you to really a final tag for now, a form tag, which will create a web form, the thing with text boxes and buttons that you and I use every day on any number of websites.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.42,1:34:57.20,英文,,0,0,0,,Inside of this form, I'm going to have an input, like a text box, whose name is going to be Q for query, because I'm trying to reimplement Google here.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.20,1:35:01.79,英文,,0,0,0,,The type of that, I want to be a text box
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.79,1:35:05.63,英文,,0,0,0,,Or if I know I'm using this for search, I can actually change this to a search box.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.63,1:35:09.49,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's going to let me, it's going to generally put a little x there so you can clear it quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.49,1:35:11.93,英文,,0,0,0,,That's a nice little enhancement as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.93,1:35:15.47,英文,,0,0,0,,And then I'm going to give myself a Submit button by doing input.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.47,1:35:21.11,英文,,0,0,0,,Whoops, I'm going to give myself a Submit button by doing input type equals Submit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.11,1:35:24.37,英文,,0,0,0,,And then I'll leave that as such here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.37,1:35:27.27,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, now I need to do a little bit more. But let's see how this looks.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.27,1:35:29.31,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go over to my other tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.31,1:35:31.19,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go back to my index.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.19,1:35:33.46,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I zoom out.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.46,1:35:36.58,英文,,0,0,0,,There is search.html. I'll click it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.58,1:35:39.04,英文,,0,0,0,,And there's not much going on here, even if I zoom in.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.04,1:35:43.00,英文,,0,0,0,,But I do, indeed, have a really big text box and a Submit button.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.00,1:35:50.35,英文,,0,0,0,,But I haven't, in my HTML, told anyone anywhere that I want this input, whether I type cat or dog, to go to google.com.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.35,1:35:55.89,英文,,0,0,0,,So for that, I need a couple of more attributes. And I know this from having done this before, and any online reference will say the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.89,1:35:59.79,英文,,0,0,0,,You can add an action attribute, like, what do you want the action of this form to be?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.79,1:36:03.57,英文,,0,0,0,,And you can put the URL to which you want this form to be submitted.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.57,1:36:10.17,英文,,0,0,0,,And I know from tinkering that it should be https://www.google.com search.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.17,1:36:16.80,英文,,0,0,0,,I don't need to put any question marks here myself, but I do want the, browser to do that for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.80,1:36:19.18,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me go back to my other tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.18,1:36:20.14,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me reload.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.14,1:36:22.16,英文,,0,0,0,,And nothing visually has happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.16,1:36:32.89,英文,,0,0,0,,But watch this. When I now type in cats, but before I hit Enter, notice that I'm currently at some long, crazy URL slash search.html is expected.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.89,1:36:38.92,英文,,0,0,0,,If I now go down to the Submit button and click Submit, watch what happens to the URL and the page itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.92,1:36:41.82,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm whisked away to the actual google.com.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.82,1:36:43.22,英文,,0,0,0,,And indeed, there are those same cats.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.22,1:36:49.76,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I zoom in here, you'll see that my URL has changed to be indeed slash search question mark q equals cats.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.76,1:36:51.34,英文,,0,0,0,,So this is just how web forms work.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.34,1:37:03.57,英文,,0,0,0,,When you submit any form on the web in this way, the browser automatically goes to that action URL, adds a question mark, puts any key value pairs that you manually typed into the text boxes, and lets the server do its thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.57,1:37:07.27,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, here's where Chrome is starting to simplify things. Safari does this too.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.27,1:37:10.63,英文,,0,0,0,,If you double-click on your URL, now you see the full URL.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.63,1:37:16.20,英文,,0,0,0,,But if any parts are missing, that's just a UI thing to eliminate visual distractions nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.20,1:37:25.64,英文,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, if I go back to my own form, if I search this time for dogs and hit Enter, now again, the URL changes to be q equals dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.64,1:37:30.99,英文,,0,0,0,,And it all reduces to this basic building block of using a form tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.99,1:37:32.35,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, I can be more explicit.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.35,1:37:40.78,英文,,0,0,0,,If I know I want to use get, which is actually the default, I can literally say, quote unquote, get in all lowercase, even though the verb earlier was by design in uppercase.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.78,1:37:43.12,英文,,0,0,0,,But here now, I'm just being ever more explicit.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.12,1:37:46.14,英文,,0,0,0,,If I don't want the label of this button,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.14,1:37:47.98,英文,,0,0,0,,to be very generically submit.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.98,1:37:50.58,英文,,0,0,0,,Maybe I want it to be Google Search, quote unquote.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.58,1:37:57.69,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, if you read the documentation for forms, you can actually change the value of the button to be, quote unquote, Google Search.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.69,1:38:01.45,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I now go back here and reload, I get a fresh form.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.45,1:38:04.89,英文,,0,0,0,,And now I get a button that literally says Google Search.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.89,1:38:19.72,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I tinker with this further, because this isn't very user-friendly, there's even more attributes I can do, I can add on my Search input, a autocomplete equals off if I don't want to see my own history for whatever reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.72,1:38:22.60,英文,,0,0,0,,I don't want people knowing I'm searching for cats and dogs on this page.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.60,1:38:28.91,英文,,0,0,0,,I can autofocus on the text box so that it shows the cursor blinking in that box by default.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.91,1:38:30.71,英文,,0,0,0,,And I can even do something like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.71,1:38:36.75,英文,,0,0,0,,I can have a placeholder attribute that says something like query or some other documentation for the user.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.75,1:38:41.76,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I now go back and reload, You'll see, notice, it says query, and it's subtle.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.76,1:38:43.88,英文,,0,0,0,,But my cursor is already positioned there.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.88,1:38:45.50,英文,,0,0,0,,It gave it focus.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.50,1:38:52.68,英文,,0,0,0,,And I can type cats now without having to click in the box manually, which is just marginally better for the user's experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.68,1:38:57.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions now on all of this here?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.73,1:38:59.77,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.77,1:39:00.65,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, that too was a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.65,1:39:02.67,英文,,0,0,0,,Why don't we take a casual five-minute break?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.67,1:39:06.43,英文,,0,0,0,,And when we resume, we'll take a look at CSS, add in some JavaScript, and then wrap up.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.43,1:39:09.37,英文,,0,0,0,,So five minutes only for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.37,1:39:11.28,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, we are back.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.28,1:39:14.16,英文,,0,0,0,,So that's technically it for HTML.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.16,1:39:20.48,英文,,0,0,0,,Here on out, it'll be up to online resources and references we point you to just to fill in your vocabulary for more tags and attributes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.48,1:39:21.80,英文,,0,0,0,,But conceptually, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.80,1:39:23.16,英文,,0,0,0,,There's attributes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.16,1:39:24.46,英文,,0,0,0,,There are tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.46,1:39:25.81,英文,,0,0,0,,And there are attributes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.81,1:39:30.47,英文,,0,0,0,,And the rest of it really is just kind of a laundry list of possible features.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.47,1:39:34.64,英文,,0,0,0,,But it turns out, too, you'll see over time that you can even see the HTML for websites.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.64,1:39:39.56,英文,,0,0,0,,So for instance, if I go over to harvard.edu in my browser.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.56,1:39:47.97,英文,,0,0,0,,which I'll go ahead in just a moment here and do here, and do HTTPS colon slash slash www.harvard.edu slash Enter.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.97,1:39:51.11,英文,,0,0,0,,It, again, will pull up today's version of Harvard's website.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.11,1:39:57.02,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I right-click or Control-click on it again and go to Inspect, you'll see those so-called developer tools.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.02,1:40:03.10,英文,,0,0,0,,And earlier, we focused on the Network tab, just so we could see the HTTP stuff going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.10,1:40:11.67,英文,,0,0,0,,But what I glossed over earlier was the so-called Elements tab, which actually shows you the HTML underlying any web page on the internet.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.67,1:40:17.26,英文,,0,0,0,,And so, for instance, here is the underlying HTML for Harvard's home page as of right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.26,1:40:19.08,英文,,0,0,0,,And aesthetically, some of it's been collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.08,1:40:25.16,英文,,0,0,0,,So if I click on these various triangles, I'll see what's actually inside of, that is, the children of some of these HTML tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.16,1:40:38.16,英文,,0,0,0,,But here on out, if you're ever curious as to how a web page made some feature visually, you can just literally use these developer tools built into your own browser just to see what the web developer actually did.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.16,1:40:41.77,英文,,0,0,0,,And you can do things, too, like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.77,1:40:53.50,英文,,0,0,0,,Maybe, let's see, if you really like this menu in the top right-hand corner of Harvard's website, you can even right-click that or Control-click that specifically, choose Inspect.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.50,1:40:57.04,英文,,0,0,0,,And what browsers will do is jump to the HTML core.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.04,1:41:00.02,英文,,0,0,0,,corresponding to that visual element on the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.02,1:41:09.72,英文,,0,0,0,,And here you can see, though we've not talked about this tag before, there's a button tag, there's an ID attribute, and there's some other attributes as well that define that button.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.72,1:41:12.90,英文,,0,0,0,,You can do other things, too, in the web page.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.90,1:41:15.01,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me scroll down, for instance, here.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.01,1:41:20.33,英文,,0,0,0,,And let's go, actually, let's go to another one, like Yale.edu here in today's theme.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.33,1:41:24.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And suppose we want to do something like,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.15,1:41:26.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Change the aesthetics of this website.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.73,1:41:29.49,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, let's do how about this over here, Life at Yale.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.49,1:41:32.03,英文,,0,0,0,,Let's right-click on this, choose Inspect.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.03,1:41:34.13,英文,,0,0,0,,That's going to jump to that part of the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.13,1:41:36.86,英文,,0,0,0,,And notice what you can do here in this Elements tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.86,1:41:41.52,英文,,0,0,0,,We can be a little playful and return today, Life at Harvard.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.52,1:41:45.74,英文,,0,0,0,,And voila, we've now changed Yale's website, it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.74,1:41:48.12,英文,,0,0,0,,So have we really?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.12,1:41:51.24,英文,,0,0,0,,Hopefully, hacking is not actually this easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.24,1:41:53.25,英文,,0,0,0,,What did we actually do?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.25,1:41:55.92,英文,,0,0,0,,Based on today's mental model.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.92,1:41:57.37,英文,,0,0,0,,Like, I have changed the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.37,1:42:05.05,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I've just changed how it is for me, right? Because my browser, just like with Phyllis and Brian from the get-go, requested Yale's web page.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.05,1:42:09.04,英文,,0,0,0,,I got back a virtual envelope containing that HTML, as we've now called it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.04,1:42:10.42,英文,,0,0,0,,My browser has a local copy.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.42,1:42:15.18,英文,,0,0,0,,It's got its own tree, otherwise known as a DOM, Document Object Model, built up in its memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.18,1:42:17.96,英文,,0,0,0,,And yeah, I went to town and changed my copy of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.96,1:42:20.90,英文,,0,0,0,,But of course, hopefully, I've not changed the actual server.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.90,1:42:25.20,英文,,0,0,0,,And in fact, if I reload Yale's website now, hopefully,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.20,1:42:29.85,英文,,0,0,0,,It will revert back to, indeed, yep, what it should be instead, life at Yale.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.85,1:42:48.15,英文,,0,0,0,,But this ability in your own browser, be it Chrome or Firefox or Edge or Safari, to have these built-in developer tools are very powerful because it's going to enable you to not only diagnose problems that will invariably arise in the coming weeks with your own code, but it's also going to allow you to learn from other sites how you can do things and tinker as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.15,1:42:53.71,英文,,0,0,0,,But up until now, we focused only on tags and attributes and on the structure of a web page.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.71,1:42:56.94,英文,,0,0,0,,Let's now focus more on the aesthetics and fine-tuning that.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.94,1:43:03.82,英文,,0,0,0,,It turns out that HTML has very limited support for anything aesthetic, like font sizes and colors and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.82,1:43:12.64,英文,,0,0,0,,And in recent years, people have used, necessarily, a second language called CSS, not a programming language, again, a markup language, if you will,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.64,1:43:17.44,英文,,0,0,0,,To just fine-tune the aesthetics of a page, font sizes, colors, margins, and all of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.44,1:43:25.71,英文,,0,0,0,,So CSS is going to allow us to define a whole bunch of properties, which is just another group of people's terminology for key-value pairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.71,1:43:34.05,英文,,0,0,0,,Indeed, ever since week 5, key-value pairs are everywhere in the world, not just at Sweetgreen and restaurants, but indeed under inline code.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.05,1:43:36.33,英文,,0,0,0,,and languages and technologies like these.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.33,1:43:41.42,英文,,0,0,0,,So properties is the new word in CSS for what a moment ago we called attributes in HTML.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.42,1:43:45.54,英文,,0,0,0,,But it's the same idea, just different vocabulary that you get used to over time.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.54,1:43:54.51,英文,,0,0,0,,A few phrases I might use now and you'll hear in the coming days would be these, type selector, class selector, ID selector, attribute selector, which just refer to
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.51,1:44:01.64,英文,,0,0,0,,Different techniques we're about to see that are going to allow you to control more precisely the aesthetics of specific things on the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.64,1:44:10.76,英文,,0,0,0,,And the way we're going to do this is we're going to take our basic HTML, like we saw earlier, and we're going to introduce in the next few minutes just a couple of more tags and or attributes, one,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.76,1:44:21.23,英文,,0,0,0,,We're going to introduce you to a tag called style, which, nicely named, allows you to control the style, the aesthetics, the visuals of the web page.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.23,1:44:27.42,英文,,0,0,0,,Or we're going to introduce you to a link tag, which, very confusingly, does not give you a link that you can click on.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.42,1:44:30.76,英文,,0,0,0,,It just links to another file that then gets automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.76,1:44:35.11,英文,,0,0,0,,Included or imported, to borrow our language from C or in Python.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.11,1:44:36.01,英文,,0,0,0,,But same idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.01,1:44:38.37,英文,,0,0,0,,This will allow us to include secondary files.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.37,1:44:48.57,英文,,0,0,0,,And we're going to ultimately show you how you can leverage third-party frameworks, libraries that other people wrote, so as to not get stuck in the weeds of all the fine-tuning of aesthetics and just make pretty things fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.57,1:44:56.10,英文,,0,0,0,,So you can focus really on the intellectually interesting part, if that's your choice, of building the content, the site out, the application out yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.10,1:44:59.02,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so with that said, let me go back to VS Code here.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.02,1:45:06.13,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me go ahead and create a simple example called home.html, like a very simple home page for John Harvard, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.13,1:45:11.89,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me give myself three paragraphs initially, the first of which is just going to have the person's name.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.89,1:45:17.54,英文,,0,0,0,,The second paragraph is going to say something like, welcome to my home page. To greet visitors.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.54,1:45:26.66,英文,,0,0,0,,And the third is going to be like a little footer, like copyright, how about John Harvard 1636, or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.66,1:45:30.24,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, let me go back to my other tab as before, reload my index.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.24,1:45:32.74,英文,,0,0,0,,There's my new file, home.html.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.74,1:45:33.78,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'll click that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.78,1:45:41.53,英文,,0,0,0,,And you'll see, OK, I mean, this is sort of 1636 style web page, super simple, all text, nothing really interesting going on there.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.53,1:45:44.05,英文,,0,0,0,,But we can start to style it a little differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.05,1:45:52.40,英文,,0,0,0,,Like, if the title of the page is John Harvard, and then it's welcome to my home page, and then this less important footer, why don't we have the text be large, then medium, then small?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.40,1:45:54.92,英文,,0,0,0,,So something arbitrary, but a little more nuanced.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.92,1:45:57.50,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me go back to VS Code here.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.50,1:46:05.53,英文,,0,0,0,,And in my home.html file, let me introduce not yet the style tag, but what I'm going to call temporarily the style attribute.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.53,1:46:06.89,英文,,0,0,0,,Both indeed exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.89,1:46:13.59,英文,,0,0,0,,This one's simpler, and it's going to be correct, but we'll see in a moment not as well designed, arguably, as is often our narrative.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.59,1:46:18.01,英文,,0,0,0,,So inside of the style tag, you can put this language called CSS.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.01,1:46:20.57,英文,,0,0,0,,Key-value pairs, otherwise known as properties.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.57,1:46:26.64,英文,,0,0,0,,The only way you know what properties exist, what keys exist, is by taking a class, reading a book, looking at an online reference.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.64,1:46:29.28,英文,,0,0,0,,And we're going to give you just a sampling of what's out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.28,1:46:33.00,英文,,0,0,0,,So suppose I want to control the font size of this first paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.00,1:46:45.75,英文,,0,0,0,,I can literally say font-size, in all lowercase, colon, and then a word like large, or I can specify 12-point, or 18-point, or something more precise like that, like from Google Docs or Microsoft Word.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.75,1:46:50.35,英文,,0,0,0,,And suppose I want to make this text down here medium.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.35,1:46:54.68,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll do, quote unquote, font-size colon medium.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.68,1:47:00.94,英文,,0,0,0,,And down here, I'll do style equals font-size small.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.94,1:47:04.12,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to start with just these three key value pairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.12,1:47:06.11,英文,,0,0,0,,Same key, but different values.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.11,1:47:08.19,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll go back to my page, and in a moment, I'll reload.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.19,1:47:13.79,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's going to be somewhat subtle, but watch how the font size do change when I reload now.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.79,1:47:15.19,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so I've got a little bigger.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.19,1:47:16.25,英文,,0,0,0,,Middle one's about the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.25,1:47:18.33,英文,,0,0,0,,And the last one is a little smaller.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.33,1:47:22.12,英文,,0,0,0,,What if I want to center it, just like many web pages have the text like this centered?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.12,1:47:25.04,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, I can separate these key value pairs with semicolons.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.04,1:47:28.38,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm sorry, semicolons are kind of sort of back with CSS.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.38,1:47:31.72,英文,,0,0,0,,But I can do text-align colon center.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.72,1:47:35.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Strictly speaking, I don't need the last semicolon if there's no more key value pairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.84,1:47:46.09,英文,,0,0,0,,But I'll just do it to be consistent, text-align Colon center, and then down here, after another semicolon, text align colon center.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.09,1:47:47.29,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.29,1:47:47.81,英文,,0,0,0,,Reload.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.81,1:47:50.25,英文,,0,0,0,,Now it's going to be much more obvious, the change.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.25,1:47:52.43,英文,,0,0,0,,And we now have the beginnings of a home page.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.43,1:47:55.40,英文,,0,0,0,,Still pretty basic, but at least it's a little more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.40,1:47:58.46,英文,,0,0,0,,Turns out we can do a little better with the copyright symbol.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.46,1:48:02.18,英文,,0,0,0,,Most computers actually have support for a circle with a C in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.18,1:48:05.59,英文,,0,0,0,,But you can't just do that with text like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.59,1:48:06.81,英文,,0,0,0,,There's different ways to do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.81,1:48:12.83,英文,,0,0,0,,You could copy-paste it from a website that already has it, so you don't have to figure out the magical keystroke on your Mac or PC.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.83,1:48:15.23,英文,,0,0,0,,But there's also in HTML what are called entities.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.23,1:48:25.26,英文,,0,0,0,,And you can actually specify, using hexadecimal or decimal codes, numbers like this, hash 169 semicolon after an ampersand.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.26,1:48:33.40,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is a special symbol that you can look up in any online reference for special characters that are hard or impossible to type manually at your keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.40,1:48:43.57,英文,,0,0,0,,And this, let me zoom in just so it's obvious, if I reload now, instead of being two parentheses and a C character, now it's a proper copyright symbol.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.57,1:48:49.51,英文,,0,0,0,,So you'll see these out there. They're not necessarily that frequently used nowadays, but it's good to know that they exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.51,1:48:53.91,英文,,0,0,0,,But let me go back now to my code and propose that, while correct,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.91,1:48:56.76,英文,,0,0,0,,This is arguably not very well designed.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.76,1:49:09.24,英文,,0,0,0,,And even if you've never seen HTML, never seen CSS before, what instinct might you have for why this is poorly designed? Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.24,1:49:10.33,英文,,0,0,0,,There's repetition, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.33,1:49:17.33,英文,,0,0,0,,In general, in the past several weeks, C, Python, SQL, repetition generally bad and sloppy and is not going to scale well.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.33,1:49:22.57,英文,,0,0,0,,So the repetition I think you're probably alluding to is text-aligned center, text-aligned center, text-aligned center.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.57,1:49:27.96,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, we can factor that out in CSS. The C in CSS means cascading.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.96,1:49:37.01,英文,,0,0,0,,And this means that if you move some properties to a parent or a grandparent, the children or grandchildren will inherit those properties.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.01,1:49:40.43,英文,,0,0,0,,That is, they will cascade down the family tree, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.43,1:49:45.87,英文,,0,0,0,,And so let me go ahead and remove all of these, since I claim they're indeed redundant.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.87,1:49:49.94,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me preserve just one of them by, well, let me do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.94,1:49:53.24,英文,,0,0,0,,It's not quite right to put a paragraph inside of a paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:53.24,1:49:57.04,英文,,0,0,0,,Like, that's just not a thing in English writing or in writing more generally.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.04,1:49:58.94,英文,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to do one thing first.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.94,1:50:01.80,英文,,0,0,0,,It turns out that these two are arguably not paragraphs, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:01.80,1:50:06.71,英文,,0,0,0,,This is like a header, the body, the essence of the page, and then the footer.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.71,1:50:15.59,英文,,0,0,0,,paragraph isn't quite the right English semantics, you can actually use more generically a tag that's all over the internet called div for division of the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.59,1:50:24.04,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is just a very generic term for a big rectangular region that divides the page again and again, just so that you can think about different regions.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.04,1:50:27.42,英文,,0,0,0,,Now that I have div, which really has no more meaning than that.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.42,1:50:30.04,英文,,0,0,0,,It's a division of the page, interpret as you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.04,1:50:32.00,英文,,0,0,0,,Now I can have multiple ones of these.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.00,1:50:34.77,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me go ahead and open a div tag here.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.77,1:50:37.29,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me close a new div tag here.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.29,1:50:41.51,英文,,0,0,0,,And then just to keep everything tidy, I'm going to highlight everything in between and hit Tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.51,1:50:44.42,英文,,0,0,0,,And that just automatically indents everything for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.42,1:50:47.76,英文,,0,0,0,,Now I have three divs inside of another div.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.76,1:50:48.84,英文,,0,0,0,,And that's totally fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.84,1:50:50.69,英文,,0,0,0,,This is very commonly done.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.69,1:50:54.09,英文,,0,0,0,,Now I'm going to do this, style equals quote unquote
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.09,1:50:58.17,英文,,0,0,0,,text-align colon center semicolon or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.17,1:51:01.08,英文,,0,0,0,,And now I have some cascading capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.08,1:51:07.80,英文,,0,0,0,,Now the parent of those three children, John Harvard will come to my home page, and the copyright will now all inherit that property.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.80,1:51:10.63,英文,,0,0,0,,So when I hit reload, nothing aesthetically has changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.63,1:51:13.41,英文,,0,0,0,,Whoops, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:13.41,1:51:15.53,英文,,0,0,0,,I should have done reload slightly earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.53,1:51:20.96,英文,,0,0,0,,When you use a div instead of a paragraph, it actually gets rid of the space between those paragraphs.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.96,1:51:23.16,英文,,0,0,0,,It just sandwiches them a little closer together.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.16,1:51:24.86,英文,,0,0,0,,I can fix this in another way.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.86,1:51:29.96,英文,,0,0,0,,But that aside, everything is still centered, and the text is still large, medium, and small.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.96,1:51:32.89,英文,,0,0,0,,But I should have called out that change in the paragraph spacing.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.89,1:51:35.77,英文,,0,0,0,,But we could bring that back before long if we wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.77,1:51:38.69,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, what more could I do to maybe improve this?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.69,1:51:42.66,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, strictly speaking, I don't really need that parent div, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.66,1:51:46.36,英文,,0,0,0,,Because these three divs inside already had a parent.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.36,1:51:49.74,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me actually get rid of that new div just to undo what I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.74,1:51:55.61,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll highlight this. And if you haven't seen this trick, Shift-Tab will unindent nicely, which is perhaps helpful.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.61,1:51:59.15,英文,,0,0,0,,I could just put that text align center on the body tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.15,1:52:03.97,英文,,0,0,0,,So text align colon center, quote unquote.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.97,1:52:08.91,英文,,0,0,0,,This, too, would work as well, so long as you go up the family tree, so to speak, reload.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.91,1:52:13.25,英文,,0,0,0,,And now, indeed, there's nothing aesthetically that has changed this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.25,1:52:16.13,英文,,0,0,0,,But it turns out, nowadays, the web is getting a little more sophisticated.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.13,1:52:24.12,英文,,0,0,0,,And even though you will see so many examples online in tutorials and books using div, div, div, div all over the place, there are newer semantic tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.12,1:52:28.98,英文,,0,0,0,,Semantic just means they have more meaning than this generic notion of a division.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.98,1:52:39.04,英文,,0,0,0,,a documentation for HTML, you'll see that if you want to have a header on a page, not a heading like H1, H2, but a header, there's literally nowadays a header tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.04,1:52:42.42,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is marginally better because it now says what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.42,1:52:46.09,英文,,0,0,0,,Search engines like Google and Bing can detect, oh, that's the header of the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.09,1:52:49.33,英文,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should use this and give it more prominence in the search results.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.33,1:52:53.55,英文,,0,0,0,,You can then have a main part of the page, so literally a tag called main nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.55,1:52:55.67,英文,,0,0,0,,You can literally have a footer of the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.67,1:53:02.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And again, these are often useful for, Screen readers to help recite things verbally for folks who might otherwise not be able to read them.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.15,1:53:12.96,英文,,0,0,0,,And probably these screen readers might highlight the header and the main part, but maybe might not spend time for the user on the footer, which is arguably a little less important semantically usually.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.96,1:53:19.94,英文,,0,0,0,,Or search engines, again, now know what's the header, what's the footer, what's the main part of the page, so they know what to search and analyze.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.94,1:53:25.35,英文,,0,0,0,,So this would arguably be a better design nowadays as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.35,1:53:28.13,英文,,0,0,0,,But what else remains as a problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.13,1:53:32.06,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, this is now getting a little bit more subtle and takes some experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.06,1:53:37.50,英文,,0,0,0,,But this practice of putting HTML and CSS all in the same file, it's a little sloppy.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:37.50,1:53:38.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.08,1:53:49.55,英文,,0,0,0,,Because it means I'm co-mingling my data with the presentation thereof, like the juicy stuff I care about, like John Harvard and the phrase, welcome to my home page, and all of the aesthetics that I might want to change over time.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.55,1:53:53.03,英文,,0,0,0,,And honestly, because everything is currently in one big file,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.03,1:53:59.80,英文,,0,0,0,,It's going to make it really hard for me to collaborate with a classmate or a colleague at work so that maybe I do the HTML, they do the CSS.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.80,1:54:02.10,英文,,0,0,0,,Like, uh-uh. Not if you're all working in the same file.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.10,1:54:02.92,英文,,0,0,0,,It would be a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.92,1:54:09.26,英文,,0,0,0,,Even if you use the VS Code sharing feature like Google Docs and both are typing at the same time, you're going to mess up somehow.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:09.26,1:54:12.13,英文,,0,0,0,,It'd be nice if we could separate these two languages.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:12.13,1:54:14.49,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, one way to do that would be as follows.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.49,1:54:21.46,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me get rid of all of the style tags, sorry, style attributes that I've added up until now.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:21.46,1:54:23.88,英文,,0,0,0,,on all four now of these tags.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.88,1:54:29.47,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me introduce the style tag that we saw on the slide earlier instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.47,1:54:39.46,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go up here into the head of the page, which is where technically these style tags must go so that they're already loaded into memory before the body is even analyzed by the browser.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.46,1:54:47.76,英文,,0,0,0,,And inside of this style tag, I'm actually going to select the HTML elements that I want to stylize, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:47.76,1:54:52.69,英文,,0,0,0,,So if I want to change the body's aesthetics, I'm going to literally type the name of that tag, body.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.69,1:55:01.43,英文,,0,0,0,,And then, I'm sorry, curly braces are back also from C. Inside of these curly braces, I'm going to put text align center.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:01.43,1:55:03.25,英文,,0,0,0,,So the key value pairs are the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.25,1:55:08.82,英文,,0,0,0,,The only new thing I've done is I've moved some of the syntax up to this new style tag in the head.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.82,1:55:13.48,英文,,0,0,0,,If I want to now control the header tag as well, I can use the same curly braces.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.48,1:55:18.50,英文,,0,0,0,,This is convention to put the open curly brace on the same line, the closed curly brace on another.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:18.50,1:55:22.32,英文,,0,0,0,,The browser doesn't really care, but this is a common CSS style convention.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.32,1:55:25.68,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to do font-size large, semicolon.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.68,1:55:29.79,英文,,0,0,0,,Then for the main tag, I'm going to do font-size medium.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.79,1:55:34.15,英文,,0,0,0,,And then for the footer tag, I'm going to do font-size small.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.15,1:55:35.33,英文,,0,0,0,,So same exact thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.33,1:55:37.51,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's admittedly a little bit more verbose.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.51,1:55:38.89,英文,,0,0,0,,It's taking up more lines of code.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.89,1:55:40.75,英文,,0,0,0,,It doesn't all quite fit on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.75,1:55:42.83,英文,,0,0,0,,But if you scroll back down now.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.83,1:55:44.59,英文,,0,0,0,,And you'll acquire an eye for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.59,1:55:45.99,英文,,0,0,0,,This is just better.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.99,1:55:47.46,英文,,0,0,0,,Like, it's just more compact.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.46,1:55:48.40,英文,,0,0,0,,It's more readable.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.40,1:55:50.88,英文,,0,0,0,,The content, the data jumps out.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.88,1:55:55.50,英文,,0,0,0,,And there's no visual distractions like the CSS properties as before.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.50,1:56:00.43,英文,,0,0,0,,Upside here, too, is that we don't actually need to, this doesn't actually change the aesthetics.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.43,1:56:03.35,英文,,0,0,0,,If I reload the same page, it still looks the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.35,1:56:07.01,英文,,0,0,0,,But I've taken a step toward some slightly better design.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.01,1:56:10.04,英文,,0,0,0,,But let me propose that there's other ways to do this, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.04,1:56:14.34,英文,,0,0,0,,We just selected things by way of their type.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:14.34,1:56:21.12,英文,,0,0,0,,So that was a so-called type selector, when I literally just specified the type of tag, body, header, main, footer.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.12,1:56:31.86,英文,,0,0,0,,But there's other ways that now we can lay the foundation for making reusable CSS that you and colleagues and classmates can use and reuse in multiple files and even in multiple projects.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.86,1:56:33.66,英文,,0,0,0,,So let me actually go ahead and do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.66,1:56:40.15,英文,,0,0,0,,Instead of just very explicitly saying, I want the body to be centered, let me invent an adjective, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.15,1:56:42.71,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me change this to .centered.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.71,1:56:48.89,英文,,0,0,0,,And this new vocabulary word, centered, will literally mean text-aligned center.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.89,1:56:50.53,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead here.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.53,1:56:58.62,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm just going to create a new adjective called large, a new adjective called medium, and a new adjective called small.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.62,1:57:02.38,英文,,0,0,0,,They are deliberately consistent with what the properties do.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:02.38,1:57:04.89,英文,,0,0,0,,But these are now my own vocabulary words.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:04.89,1:57:07.21,英文,,0,0,0,,And they are called classes.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.21,1:57:14.39,英文,,0,0,0,,So a class is just a collection of key value pairs, a collection of properties that you get to invent for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.39,1:57:16.57,英文,,0,0,0,,And what it lets you do now is this.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:16.57,1:57:25.81,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, if I want the whole body to be centered, I can add this tag, which we actually saw briefly in Yale's HTML, class="center".
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.81,1:57:31.05,英文,,0,0,0,,Down here in the header, if I want this to be large, I can say class="large".
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.05,1:57:35.34,英文,,0,0,0,,Down here on main, I can say class="medium".
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.34,1:57:38.76,英文,,0,0,0,,And down here, I can have class equals quote, unquote, small.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.76,1:57:45.50,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, I have taken one step backward by re-adding some of the aesthetics to the page, but it's not the actual properties.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:45.50,1:57:46.97,英文,,0,0,0,,It's not the key value pairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.97,1:57:58.21,英文,,0,0,0,,It's now more semantically nice, because now I just know from reading the HTML what these things are going to look like, whereas the implementation details for all four of those adjectives is now relegated up above.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.21,1:57:59.51,英文,,0,0,0,,And these are literally my words.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.51,1:58:03.17,英文,,0,0,0,,I could change it to dot foo and use class equals quote unquote foo.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.17,1:58:07.18,英文,,0,0,0,,But obviously, that would not be the best choice of words in this case.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:07.18,1:58:08.30,英文,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.30,1:58:11.34,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions on this?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.34,1:58:18.08,英文,,0,0,0,,This now is what we would call a class selector by using literally the dot, even though the dot does not appear elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:18.08,1:58:21.73,英文,,0,0,0,,But dot means this is a class.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:21.73,1:58:25.67,英文,,0,0,0,,These are not always the best syntactic design decisions that the world makes.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:25.67,1:58:27.65,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, well, one last trick then.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.65,1:58:31.09,英文,,0,0,0,,Notice that this is a little annoying that I'm still working in the same file.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:31.09,1:58:43.26,英文,,0,0,0,,And if my classmate wants to clean up my aesthetics, make my home page look way better, if my colleague wants to do the same, wouldn't it be nice if we could actually move all of this code to a different file, like a Python library or a C header file?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:43.26,1:58:44.26,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, you can.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:44.26,1:58:47.90,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead and delete that whole style tag.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.90,1:58:56.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me add a confusingly named link tag, the href of which, let's call a new file styles.css.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:56.73,1:59:00.77,英文,,0,0,0,,And let's say that the relationship of that file is that of stylesheet.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.77,1:59:03.67,英文,,0,0,0,,So this is a term of art in the world of web development.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:03.67,1:59:08.33,英文,,0,0,0,,A stylesheet is a text file that contains lots of styles, lots of CSS properties.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.33,1:59:10.82,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me open my terminal real fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:10.82,1:59:16.60,英文,,0,0,0,,And let me do code of styles.css.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.60,1:59:17.38,英文,,0,0,0,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.38,1:59:20.93,英文,,0,0,0,,And in this file, I'm going to paste all of those same lines as earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.93,1:59:22.69,英文,,0,0,0,,But now they're in a separate file.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:22.69,1:59:37.88,英文,,0,0,0,,And indeed, if I hide my terminal window and I give this file to a colleague, they can now work on the aesthetics of the page and make things a lot prettier than this, maybe use specific font sizes, maybe add colors and the like, whereas I can focus entirely on the HTML, because this file now will reference that other.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.88,1:59:48.14,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I go back to my other tab and reload, the content's going to be exactly the same, but now I'm using some separate file instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:48.14,1:59:53.91,英文,,0,0,0,,Any questions now about these techniques here?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.91,2:00:00.25,英文,,0,0,0,,All right, so with that said, let me show just one example now of what I called a moment ago frameworks.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.25,2:00:12.16,英文,,0,0,0,,And this is where web development gets kind of fun, at least if you like this, especially if you like the sort of logical design, the presentation of information you care about, but you really don't want to struggle with font sizes and colors and getting everything pixel perfect, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:12.16,2:00:21.65,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me propose that I open up here an example in just a moment in VS Code that I prepared in advance, and this one is going to be
Dialogue: 0,2:00:21.65,2:00:32.23,英文,,0,0,0,,an opportunity to consider how you might take some of the data from last week, wherein we collected everyone's favorites, and lay it out in a really big HTML table.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:32.23,2:00:34.43,英文,,0,0,0,,So I wrote this out in advance because it was a huge amount of data.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:34.43,2:00:37.21,英文,,0,0,0,,But it's the same data from the Google form from last week.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:37.21,2:00:41.08,英文,,0,0,0,,And you'll see already the hints of a table tag and these TRs.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.08,2:00:43.36,英文,,0,0,0,,And I added a few other tags for aesthetics.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:43.36,2:00:47.08,英文,,0,0,0,,It turns out when you have a more visually interesting header for your table,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:47.08,2:00:48.94,英文,,0,0,0,,There's another tag called t-head.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:48.94,2:00:50.58,英文,,0,0,0,,There's another tag called t-body.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:50.58,2:00:52.50,英文,,0,0,0,,These are not all that intellectually interesting.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:52.50,2:00:58.28,英文,,0,0,0,,I just read the documentation and realized, oh, to make things prettier, I need a t-head, a t-body, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:58.28,2:01:13.61,英文,,0,0,0,,But what's interesting here is that if I go to my index here and open this file called favorites.html, here is all of the data from last week's Google spreadsheet, which we exported as CSV and I manually, before class, converted to just HTML.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:13.61,2:01:14.83,英文,,0,0,0,,It's indeed a table.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:14.83,2:01:16.19,英文,,0,0,0,,But it's really not pretty.
