Dialogue: 0,2:01:20.53,2:01:23.17,英文,,0,0,0,,But this is just raw HTML written by me.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:23.17,2:01:27.93,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, I could use CSS and some of the tricks we just saw to maybe change font size.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:27.93,2:01:31.73,英文,,0,0,0,,There's ways to change color, background color, and a lot of things like that.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:31.73,2:01:37.20,英文,,0,0,0,,But honestly, surely other people in the world have presented tabular data in pretty ways, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:37.20,2:01:40.18,英文,,0,0,0,,I've been to many websites that have prettier tables than mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:40.18,2:01:50.26,英文,,0,0,0,,Can I maybe use someone else's framework, someone else's CSS, include it in my page, but then stand on their shoulders and just make my stuff look prettier?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:50.26,2:01:51.48,英文,,0,0,0,,Well, I dare say I can.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:51.48,2:01:54.20,英文,,0,0,0,,Let me go ahead here and semi-secretly
Dialogue: 0,2:01:54.20,2:02:06.53,英文,,0,0,0,,Open up VS Code again, and let me grab a slightly different version of favorites.html that I also opened in advance, wherein I add this line of code instead.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:06.53,2:02:08.73,英文,,0,0,0,,Give me just a moment to foreground this version.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:08.73,2:02:13.21,英文,,0,0,0,,And the data is all the same as before, but I've added one of these link tags.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:13.21,2:02:19.47,英文,,0,0,0,,And I'm not linking to my own styles.css. I'm using a popular library called Bootstrap.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:19.47,2:02:36.44,英文,,0,0,0,,And Bootstrap is just one of many popular libraries out there, free at that, that has a whole bunch of CSS files and soon JavaScript files that you can just use for free in your own projects, personally or professionally, that just make things look and behave better without you having to reinvent wheels.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:36.44,2:02:41.74,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, to access their CSS, I had to read their documentation and grab this very long URL here.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:41.74,2:02:45.56,英文,,0,0,0,,But it's the same idea, link a for tref equals quote unquote something.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.56,2:02:48.60,英文,,0,0,0,,And I read their documentation, and they told me to add this.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:48.60,2:03:00.71,英文,,0,0,0,,They told me that if I want my tables to be prettier, I have to add a class attribute to my own table tag and specify, a little weirdly, but this is what Bootstrap told me to do, a class called table.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:00.71,2:03:03.26,英文,,0,0,0,,And that will make it a prettier Bootstrap table.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:03.26,2:03:14.26,英文,,0,0,0,,And if I want to stripe it, like every other row is gray instead of white, just to make it pop a little more visually, I can also add a second class separated by a space called table striped.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:14.26,2:03:15.38,英文,,0,0,0,,That's all I did.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:15.38,2:03:18.87,英文,,0,0,0,,I added line 5, and I changed line 9, and that is it.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:18.87,2:03:22.47,英文,,0,0,0,,The rest of the hundreds of lines in favorites.html are the same.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:22.47,2:03:29.47,英文,,0,0,0,,But if I go back here now and reload the browser, now, thanks to Bootstrap, voila, like it's much prettier.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:29.47,2:03:32.69,英文,,0,0,0,,Now I can zoom out, and that changes the font size just locally for me.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:32.69,2:03:38.55,英文,,0,0,0,,And even if you don't love their aesthetics, I mean, this is easily better than my own there.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:38.55,2:03:42.43,英文,,0,0,0,,And it turns out we can do even better by adding interactivity to this, too.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:42.43,2:03:45.92,英文,,0,0,0,,But to do that, we're going to need one final language for today.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:45.92,2:03:48.58,英文,,0,0,0,,And this one is an actual programming language.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:48.58,2:04:00.67,英文,,0,0,0,,And we won't use it all that much in CS50, but we introduce it here as we begin web stuff because there's just so many free libraries and professional libraries that you can use just to make your web applications fancier and more interactive.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:00.67,2:04:08.77,英文,,0,0,0,,Mobile applications, as well, increasingly use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to power our iPhones and Android devices, as well.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:08.77,2:04:16.18,英文,,0,0,0,,So a quick tour of some syntax, and then we'll conclude with just some hopefully inspiring examples to give you a taste of what JavaScript can do.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:16.18,2:04:20.26,英文,,0,0,0,,So JavaScript supports conditionals, just like C and Python before it.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:20.26,2:04:23.70,英文,,0,0,0,,If we rewind to our scratch days, here, of course, is a conditional.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:23.70,2:04:26.58,英文,,0,0,0,,Here is the corresponding JavaScript code as of today.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:26.58,2:04:30.44,英文,,0,0,0,,It's pretty much identical to C with the syntax here.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:30.44,2:04:34.26,英文,,0,0,0,,If we had an if else, in Scratch it looked like this.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:34.26,2:04:36.18,英文,,0,0,0,,In JavaScript, it's going to look like this instead.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:36.18,2:04:45.43,英文,,0,0,0,,So it's a bit of a regression vis-a-vis Python, like the parentheses are back, the curly braces are back, the semicolons I mentioned in CSS are also back in JavaScript potentially.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:45.43,2:04:47.25,英文,,0,0,0,,But it's familiar is the point here.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:47.25,2:04:53.99,英文,,0,0,0,,And it's a different language that's frequently used for the web, whereas you can't use Python in the ways we're about to use JavaScript.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:53.99,2:04:56.53,英文,,0,0,0,,It just wasn't designed for that purpose.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:56.53,2:05:04.60,英文,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, if you have an else if else in Scratch, well, in JavaScript, just like in C, it's going to look like this instead.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:04.60,2:05:06.92,英文,,0,0,0,,Variables in JavaScript, of course, are a thing, too.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:06.92,2:05:10.26,英文,,0,0,0,,And in Scratch, we might have initialized a counter variable to 0.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:10.26,2:05:13.18,英文,,0,0,0,,In JavaScript, a few different ways to do this.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:13.18,2:05:15.36,英文,,0,0,0,,And just for now, the keyword is let.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:15.36,2:05:20.55,英文,,0,0,0,,It's sort of a polite way of asking for a variable, let. Counter equals zero semicolon.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.55,2:05:24.75,英文,,0,0,0,,So you don't mention the type, but you do use a keyword here in this case called let.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:24.75,2:05:27.79,英文,,0,0,0,,If you want to increment counter by one, a few different ways.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:27.79,2:05:33.23,英文,,0,0,0,,In JavaScript, you can do this, just like in C. In JavaScript, you can do this, just like in C and in Python.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:33.23,2:05:34.95,英文,,0,0,0,,In JavaScript, you can also get this.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:34.95,2:05:36.17,英文,,0,0,0,,So plus plus is back.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:36.17,2:05:38.97,英文,,0,0,0,,So maybe that counterbalances the other syntax as well.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:38.97,2:05:41.19,英文,,0,0,0,,That was not the case in Python.
